{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486618887,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sNVSDJv5PuJ2NA56UsuZlZSm","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md","offset":54,"limit":170},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n54: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n55: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n56: \n57: ### Problem Statement\n58: `deep-loop-workflows` is already Option-E-hub-shaped but carries the wrong top-level name; `deep-loop-runtime` is a separate skill folder that `deep-loop-workflows`' mode packets already reach into via hardcoded relative paths in 12+ files, and which itself reaches back into `deep-loop-workflows/shared/rollout/` in 5+ files, plus borrows TypeScript tooling from a third skill (`system-spec-kit`) via 4 more hardcoded relative paths. None of this is expressed as a formal dependency ŌĆö it's silent, depth-sensitive relative addressing that a naive move breaks.\n59: \n60: ### Purpose\n61: Execute the irreversible physical merge: rename `deep-loop-workflows` ŌåÆ `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` inside it as `runtime/` (infrastructure, not a mode ŌĆö no `graph-metadata.json`, `SKILL.md` demoted to `README.md`), repair every coupling site at its new correct depth, and fresh-author the unified identity.\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n67: ## 3. SCOPE\n68: \n69: ### In Scope\n70: - `git mv .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop`; identity-field edits inside that tree only (Stage 1).\n71: - `git mv .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime`; delete its `graph-metadata.json`; demote `SKILL.md` ŌåÆ `README.md` (Stage 2).\n72: - Repair 5+ forward-coupling sites (`runtime` ŌåÆ workflows-content, same hop-count, delete `deep-loop-workflows` segment) and 12+ reverse-coupling sites (workflows-content ŌåÆ `runtime`, minus-one hop, rename segment) (Stage 3a).\n73: - Repair the 4-site `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow (Stage 3b) ŌĆö this is load-bearing test wiring, not documentation, and must land in this phase, not be handed to child 003.\n74: - Fresh-author `system-deep-loop/graph-metadata.json`; bump to `2.0.0.0`; write `changelog/v2.0.0.0.md` (Stage 4).\n75: \n76: ### Out of Scope\n77: - Any reference outside the `system-deep-loop/` tree itself (commands, agents, READMEs, advisor corpus, sibling `graph-metadata.json` edges) ŌĆö that's child 003.\n78: - Wiring `fallback-router.ts` ŌĆö child 004, optional.\n79: - Genuine TypeScript-tooling decoupling of `runtime/` from `system-spec-kit` (giving it its own local `typescript`/`@types`) ŌĆö follow-up hardening, not this phase.\n80: \n81: ### Files to Change\n82: \n83: | File Path | Change Type | Description |\n84: |-----------|-------------|-------------|\n85: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/**` ŌåÆ `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/**` | Move + edit | Whole tree; identity fields updated |\n86: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/**` ŌåÆ `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/**` | Move + edit | Whole tree incl. `database/`; `graph-metadata.json` deleted; `SKILL.md`ŌåÆ`README.md` |\n87: | `runtime/scripts/{render-command-contract,compile-command-contracts,check-contract-drift,fanout-run}.cjs` | Edit | Forward-coupling path repair (delete segment) |\n88: | 7 files in `runtime/tests/unit/*.vitest.ts` | Edit | Forward-coupling path repair (delete segment) |\n89: | `{deep-research,deep-review,deep-improvement,deep-ai-council}/scripts/**` (12 files) | Edit | Reverse-coupling path repair (minus-one hop, rename segment) |\n90: | `runtime/package.json`, `runtime/tsconfig.json` | Edit | `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, one more `..` |\n91: | `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json`, `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` | Edit | Reverse half of the tooling-borrow, expand target path |\n92: | `system-deep-loop/graph-metadata.json` | Create (fresh-author) | The one unified identity |\n93: | `system-deep-loop/changelog/v2.0.0.0.md` | Create | Reunification changelog entry |\n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n99: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n100: \n101: ### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)\n102: \n103: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n104: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n105: | REQ-001 | Physical move preserves git history | `git log --follow -- .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/observability-events.jsonl` surfaces pre-move commits |\n106: | REQ-002 | Both coupling directions repaired correctly (not backwards) | `cd .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime && npm test` green; a live `/deep:research` or `/deep:review` short run confirms reverse-direction `require()`s resolve at execution time |\n107: | REQ-003 | `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repaired | `npm run typecheck` in `runtime/` succeeds; `npm run test:council` in `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` succeeds |\n108: | REQ-004 | Exactly one `graph-metadata.json` | `find .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop -iname graph-metadata.json \\| wc -l` == 1 |\n109: | REQ-005 | Durable state preserved byte-identical | SQLite checksums and `observability-events.jsonl` line count match pre-move snapshot |\n110: \n111: ### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n112: \n113: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n114: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n115: | REQ-006 | No in-flight loop or stale writer-lock at move time | Pre-move quiesce check passes |\n116: | REQ-007 | `package_skill.py --check` passes on the renamed hub and all 4 mode packets | Clean check output |\n117: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n118: \n119: ---\n120: \n121: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n122: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n123: \n124: - **SC-001**: `system-deep-loop/` exists with `runtime/` nested inside; `deep-loop-workflows/` and `deep-loop-runtime/` no longer exist.\n125: - **SC-002**: `grep -rn \"deep-loop-workflows\\|deep-loop-runtime\" .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop --include=\"*.cjs\" --include=\"*.ts\"` returns zero hits outside changelog/README prose.\n126: - **SC-003**: Version `2.0.0.0` consistent across `SKILL.md`, `mode-registry.json`, `hub-router.json`, `description.json`.\n127: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n132: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n133: \n134: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n135: |------|------|--------|------------|\n136: | Risk | Directional asymmetry (Class A adds nothing/deletes a segment; Class B removes one hop) is the single highest-probability mechanical failure mode | High | Explicit before/after table per site (plan.md ┬¦3); exit gate is a real `npm test` run, not a grep |\n137: | Risk | Live git-tracked state + 2 writer-locked SQLite DBs mid-move | Medium | Stage 0 quiesce: zero stale/live writer-lock files, zero running `convergence.cjs`/`fanout-run.cjs` process, checksum before/after |\n138: | Risk | `system-spec-kit`'s tooling-borrow falls into the gap between this phase and child 003 | Medium (silent coverage hole, not a build failure) | Explicitly scoped INTO this phase (Stage 3b), not child 003 |\n139: | Dependency | 001-reference-research's synthesis may revise this design before execution | ŌĆö | This phase does not start until 001 completes |\n140: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n145: ## 7. OPEN QUESTIONS\n146: \n147: - None blocking; awaiting 001's research synthesis before execution.\n148: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n149: \n150: ---\n151: \n152: ## 8. ARCHITECTURE ADDENDUM (Level 3)\n153: \n154: ### Target layout\n155: \n156: ```\n157: system-deep-loop/\n158:   SKILL.md  README.md  description.json  mode-registry.json  hub-router.json  graph-metadata.json\n159:   changelog/                    # v1.0.0.0, v1.1.0.0 preserved + NEW v2.0.0.0\n160:   deep-research/  deep-review/  deep-ai-council/  deep-improvement/   # untouched\n161:   shared/{behavior-benchmark,progress,rollout,synthesis}/             # untouched, stays at hub level\n162:   benchmark/  manual_testing_playbook/                                 # untouched\n163:   runtime/                      # nested former deep-loop-runtime, NO graph-metadata.json\n164:     README.md  package.json  tsconfig.json  vitest.config.ts  node_modules/\n165:     lib/{deep-loop,coverage-graph,council}/  scripts/  tests/  database/\n166:     feature_catalog/  references/  changelog/ (frozen at v1.5.0.1)  manual_testing_playbook/\n167: ```\n168: \n169: `runtime/` is infrastructure, not a `workflowMode` ŌĆö it has no command, no agent, no `artifactRoot`. Adding it as an 8th `mode-registry.json` entry would be a category error.\n170: \n171: ### Path-repair rule (the one insight that governs everything)\n172: \n173: - **Forward** (`runtime` ŌåÆ workflows-content): both sides moved one level deeper in lockstep ŌåÆ hop-count **unchanged**, delete the `deep-loop-workflows` segment.\n174: - **Reverse** (workflows-content ŌåÆ `runtime`): `runtime` got nearer (from top-level sibling to hub child) ŌåÆ **minus one hop**, rename the segment.\n175: \n176: ### Version strategy\n177: \n178: `2.0.0.0`, not a continuation of either lineage (`1.1.0.0` workflows / `1.5.0.1` runtime) ŌĆö signals \"second era\" of the family (era 1 = the FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP split into two skills; era 2 = reunification). Both prior changelogs preserved in place and frozen; one new changelog going forward.\n\n(End of file - total 178 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n`deep-loop-workflows` is already Option-E-hub-shaped but carries the wrong top-level name; `deep-loop-runtime` is a separate skill folder that `deep-loop-workflows`' mode packets already reach into via hardcoded relative paths in 12+ files, and which itself reaches back into `deep-loop-workflows/shared/rollout/` in 5+ files, plus borrows TypeScript tooling from a third skill (`system-spec-kit`) via 4 more hardcoded relative paths. None of this is expressed as a formal dependency ŌĆö it's silent, depth-sensitive relative addressing that a naive move breaks.\n\n### Purpose\nExecute the irreversible physical merge: rename `deep-loop-workflows` ŌåÆ `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` inside it as `runtime/` (infrastructure, not a mode ŌĆö no `graph-metadata.json`, `SKILL.md` demoted to `README.md`), repair every coupling site at its new correct depth, and fresh-author the unified identity.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- `git mv .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop`; identity-field edits inside that tree only (Stage 1).\n- `git mv .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime`; delete its `graph-metadata.json`; demote `SKILL.md` ŌåÆ `README.md` (Stage 2).\n- Repair 5+ forward-coupling sites (`runtime` ŌåÆ workflows-content, same hop-count, delete `deep-loop-workflows` segment) and 12+ reverse-coupling sites (workflows-content ŌåÆ `runtime`, minus-one hop, rename segment) (Stage 3a).\n- Repair the 4-site `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow (Stage 3b) ŌĆö this is load-bearing test wiring, not documentation, and must land in this phase, not be handed to child 003.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md","text":"<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n`deep-loop-workflows` is already Option-E-hub-shaped but carries the wrong top-level name; `deep-loop-runtime` is a separate skill folder that `deep-loop-workflows`' mode packets already reach into via hardcoded relative paths in 12+ files, and which itself reaches back into `deep-loop-workflows/shared/rollout/` in 5+ files, plus borrows TypeScript tooling from a third skill (`system-spec-kit`) via 4 more hardcoded relative paths. None of this is expressed as a formal dependency ŌĆö it's silent, depth-sensitive relative addressing that a naive move breaks.\n\n### Purpose\nExecute the irreversible physical merge: rename `deep-loop-workflows` ŌåÆ `system-deep-loop`, nest `deep-loop-runtime` inside it as `runtime/` (infrastructure, not a mode ŌĆö no `graph-metadata.json`, `SKILL.md` demoted to `README.md`), repair every coupling site at its new correct depth, and fresh-author the unified identity.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- `git mv .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop`; identity-field edits inside that tree only (Stage 1).\n- `git mv .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime`; delete its `graph-metadata.json`; demote `SKILL.md` ŌåÆ `README.md` (Stage 2).\n- Repair 5+ forward-coupling sites (`runtime` ŌåÆ workflows-content, same hop-count, delete `deep-loop-workflows` segment) and 12+ reverse-coupling sites (workflows-content ŌåÆ `runtime`, minus-one hop, rename segment) (Stage 3a).\n- Repair the 4-site `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow (Stage 3b) ŌĆö this is load-bearing test wiring, not documentation, and must land in this phase, not be handed to child 003.\n- Fresh-author `system-deep-loop/graph-metadata.json`; bump to `2.0.0.0`; write `changelog/v2.0.0.0.md` (Stage 4).\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Any reference outside the `system-deep-loop/` tree itself (commands, agents, READMEs, advisor corpus, sibling `graph-metadata.json` edges) ŌĆö that's child 003.\n- Wiring `fallback-router.ts` ŌĆö child 004, optional.\n- Genuine TypeScript-tooling decoupling of `runtime/` from `system-spec-kit` (giving it its own local `typescript`/`@types`) ŌĆö follow-up hardening, not this phase.\n\n### Files to Change\n\n| File Path | Change Type | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|-------------|\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/**` ŌåÆ `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/**` | Move + edit | Whole tree; identity fields updated |\n| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/**` ŌåÆ `.opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/**` | Move + edit | Whole tree incl. `database/`; `graph-metadata.json` deleted; `SKILL.md`ŌåÆ`README.md` |\n| `runtime/scripts/{render-command-contract,compile-command-contracts,check-contract-drift,fanout-run}.cjs` | Edit | Forward-coupling path repair (delete segment) |\n| 7 files in `runtime/tests/unit/*.vitest.ts` | Edit | Forward-coupling path repair (delete segment) |\n| `{deep-research,deep-review,deep-improvement,deep-ai-council}/scripts/**` (12 files) | Edit | Reverse-coupling path repair (minus-one hop, rename segment) |\n| `runtime/package.json`, `runtime/tsconfig.json` | Edit | `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, one more `..` |\n| `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json`, `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` | Edit | Reverse half of the tooling-borrow, expand target path |\n| `system-deep-loop/graph-metadata.json` | Create (fresh-author) | The one unified identity |\n| `system-deep-loop/changelog/v2.0.0.0.md` | Create | Reunification changelog entry |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | Physical move preserves git history | `git log --follow -- .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime/database/observability-events.jsonl` surfaces pre-move commits |\n| REQ-002 | Both coupling directions repaired correctly (not backwards) | `cd .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop/runtime && npm test` green; a live `/deep:research` or `/deep:review` short run confirms reverse-direction `require()`s resolve at execution time |\n| REQ-003 | `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repaired | `npm run typecheck` in `runtime/` succeeds; `npm run test:council` in `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` succeeds |\n| REQ-004 | Exactly one `graph-metadata.json` | `find .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop -iname graph-metadata.json \\| wc -l` == 1 |\n| REQ-005 | Durable state preserved byte-identical | SQLite checksums and `observability-events.jsonl` line count match pre-move snapshot |\n\n### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-006 | No in-flight loop or stale writer-lock at move time | Pre-move quiesce check passes |\n| REQ-007 | `package_skill.py --check` passes on the renamed hub and all 4 mode packets | Clean check output |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: `system-deep-loop/` exists with `runtime/` nested inside; `deep-loop-workflows/` and `deep-loop-runtime/` no longer exist.\n- **SC-002**: `grep -rn \"deep-loop-workflows\\|deep-loop-runtime\" .opencode/skills/system-deep-loop --include=\"*.cjs\" --include=\"*.ts\"` returns zero hits outside changelog/README prose.\n- **SC-003**: Version `2.0.0.0` consistent across `SKILL.md`, `mode-registry.json`, `hub-router.json`, `description.json`.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Risk | Directional asymmetry (Class A adds nothing/deletes a segment; Class B removes one hop) is the single highest-probability mechanical failure mode | High | Explicit before/after table per site (plan.md ┬¦3); exit gate is a real `npm test` run, not a grep |\n| Risk | Live git-tracked state + 2 writer-locked SQLite DBs mid-move | Medium | Stage 0 quiesce: zero stale/live writer-lock files, zero running `convergence.cjs`/`fanout-run.cjs` process, checksum before/after |\n| Risk | `system-spec-kit`'s tooling-borrow falls into the gap between this phase and child 003 | Medium (silent coverage hole, not a build failure) | Explicitly scoped INTO this phase (Stage 3b), not child 003 |\n| Dependency | 001-reference-research's synthesis may revise this design before execution | ŌĆö | This phase does not start until 001 completes |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 7. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- None blocking; awaiting 001's research synthesis before execution.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. ARCHITECTURE ADDENDUM (Level 3)\n\n### Target layout\n\n```\nsystem-deep-loop/\n  SKILL.md  README.md  description.json  mode-registry.json  hub-router.json  graph-metadata.json\n  changelog/                    # v1.0.0.0, v1.1.0.0 preserved + NEW v2.0.0.0\n  deep-research/  deep-review/  deep-ai-council/  deep-improvement/   # untouched\n  shared/{behavior-benchmark,progress,rollout,synthesis}/             # untouched, stays at hub level\n  benchmark/  manual_testing_playbook/                                 # untouched\n  runtime/                      # nested former deep-loop-runtime, NO graph-metadata.json\n    README.md  package.json  tsconfig.json  vitest.config.ts  node_modules/\n    lib/{deep-loop,coverage-graph,council}/  scripts/  tests/  database/\n    feature_catalog/  references/  changelog/ (frozen at v1.5.0.1)  manual_testing_playbook/\n```\n\n`runtime/` is infrastructure, not a `workflowMode` ŌĆö it has no command, no agent, no `artifactRoot`. Adding it as an 8th `mode-registry.json` entry would be a category error.\n\n### Path-repair rule (the one insight that governs everything)\n\n- **Forward** (`runtime` ŌåÆ workflows-content): both sides moved one level deeper in lockstep ŌåÆ hop-count **unchanged**, delete the `deep-loop-workflows` segment.\n- **Reverse** (workflows-content ŌåÆ `runtime`): `runtime` got nearer (from top-level sibling to hub child) ŌåÆ **minus one hop**, rename the segment.\n\n### Version strategy\n\n`2.0.0.0`, not a continuation of either lineage (`1.1.0.0` workflows / `1.5.0.1` runtime) ŌĆö signals \"second era\" of the family (era 1 = the FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP split into two skills; era 2 = reunification). Both prior changelogs preserved in place and frozen; one new changelog going forward.","lineStart":54,"lineEnd":178,"totalLines":178,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md","time":{"start":1783486618856,"end":1783486618874}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08955fafb0883e03016a4dd89acecc8191b555f06293c5a26e"}},"id":"prt_f40161cd0001LxLcHao3MgZLZZ","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4015fc72001ZYPVcn7DwPPQdc"}}
