lure and a decoupling failure indistinguishable during validation. Tracked as follow-up hardening, out of scope.\n100: \n101: ### `graph-metadata.json` consolidation\n102: \n103: Fresh-author (not N-way merge), matching the 154 precedent. Carry forward `depends_on: system-spec-kit`, `enhances: system-spec-kit`, `siblings: sk-prompt`. Drop the `deep-loop-runtime Ōåö deep-loop-workflows` edges entirely ŌĆö they become intra-skill structure. Preserve `deep-loop-runtime`'s `packet_id: \"116-deep-skill-evolution\"` lineage narratively (this packet's spec.md + the new `changelog/v2.0.0.0.md`), not structurally.\n104: <!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n105: \n106: ---\n107: \n108: <!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n109: ## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n110: \n111: ### Phase 1: Setup (Stage 0 ŌĆö pre-flight, no tracked-file changes)\n112: - [ ] Establish recovery baseline (worktree snapshot or pre-move tag).\n113: - [ ] Quiesce: confirm zero in-flight `/deep:*` sessions, zero stale writer-lock files under `runtime/database/`.\n114: - [ ] Capture baseline: `cd deep-loop-runtime && npm test` (expect 47 files/379 tests; tolerate one known rerun-clearable flake in `loop-lock.vitest.ts`).\n115: - [ ] Snapshot SQLite checksums + `observability-events.jsonl` line count.\n116: \n117: ### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n118: - [ ] **Stage 1**: `git mv deep-loop-workflows system-deep-loop`; edit identity fields (`SKILL.md`, `description.json`, `mode-registry.json`, `hub-router.json`, `graph-metadata.json` `skill_id`, README title) inside that tree only.\n119: - [ ] **Stage 2**: `git mv deep-loop-runtime system-deep-loop/runtime`; delete `runtime/graph-metadata.json`; demote `runtime/SKILL.md` ŌåÆ `runtime/README.md` (strip routable-skill frontmatter, keep content).\n120: - [ ] **Stage 3a**: apply Class A + Class B path repairs above.\n121: - [ ] **Stage 3b**: apply the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repairs above.\n122: - [ ] **Stage 4**: fresh-author `graph-metadata.json`; bump version to `2.0.0.0` across `SKILL.md`/`description.json`/`mode-registry.json`/`hub-router.json`; write `changelog/v2.0.0.0.md`.\n123: \n124: ### Phase 3: Verification\n125: - [ ] `package_skill.py --check` on the renamed hub and all 4 mode packets.\n126: - [ ] `find system-deep-loop -iname graph-metadata.json | wc -l` == 1.\n127: - [ ] `cd system-deep-loop/runtime && npm test` green (tolerate the known flake).\n128: - [ ] `cd system-deep-loop/runtime && npm run typecheck` succeeds.\n129: - [ ] `cd system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npm run test:council` succeeds.\n130: - [ ] `git log --follow -- system-deep-loop/runtime/database/observability-events.jsonl` surfaces pre-move commits; SQLite checksums + jsonl line count match Stage-0 snapshot.\n131: - [ ] A live `/deep:research` or `/deep:review` short run confirms reverse-direction `require()`s resolve at execution time.\n132: <!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n137: ## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n138: \n139: | Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n140: |-----------|-------|-------|\n141: | Unit/integration | `runtime/`'s full vitest suite | `npm test` inside `runtime/` |\n142: | Cross-skill integration | `system-spec-kit`'s council test glob | `npm run test:council` in `mcp_server/` |\n143: | Static | Residual grep for old names inside code paths | `grep -rn \"deep-loop-workflows\\|deep-loop-runtime\" system-deep-loop --include=\"*.cjs\" --include=\"*.ts\"` |\n144: | Live | Real loop dispatch confirms reverse `require()`s resolve | A short `/deep:research` or `/deep:review` run |\n145: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: <!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n150: ## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n151: \n152: | Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n153: |------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n154: | 001-reference-research synthesis | Internal | Pending | This phase does not start until 001 completes |\n155: | Git rename-detection (`-M`/similarity) | Tooling | Confirmed reliable at both directory 