8` (5 requires) | 3 ups | 2 ups, rename |\n| `deep-ai-council/scripts/tests/*.vitest.ts` (nested one level deeper) | 4 ups | 3 ups, rename |\n| `deep-improvement/scripts/shared/improvement-journal.cjs:24` | 4 ups | 3 ups, rename |\n| `deep-improvement/scripts/shared/reduce-state.cjs:124` (`path.join` array form) | `path.join(__dirname,'..','..','..','..','deep-loop-runtime','lib','deep-loop')` | `path.join(__dirname,'..','..','..','runtime','lib','deep-loop')` |\n\nAll 12 files follow this pattern regardless of depth (`scripts/` = 3ŌåÆ2 ups; `scripts/{tests,shared}/` = 4ŌåÆ3 ups).\n\n### `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow (Stage 3b, load-bearing ŌĆö do not defer to child 003)\n\n| File | Before | After |\n|---|---|---|\n| `runtime/package.json` `typecheck` script | `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc ...` | `../../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc ...` |\n| `runtime/tsconfig.json` `typeRoots` | `[\"../system-spec-kit/node_modules/@types\"]` | `[\"../../system-spec-kit/node_modules/@types\"]` |\n| `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json` `test:council` | `../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts` | `../../system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-script.vitest.ts` |\n| `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` include glob | `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` | `'../system-deep-loop/runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` |\n\nDecision: fix paths only, do not decouple `runtime/`'s TypeScript tooling from `system-spec-kit` in this phase ŌĆö bundling a decoupling change would make a merge failure and a decoupling failure indistinguishable during validation. Tracked as follow-up hardening, out of scope.\n\n### `graph-metadata.json` consolidation\n\nFresh-author (not N-way merge), matching the 154 precedent. Carry forward `depends_on: system-spec-kit`, `enhances: system-spec-kit`, `siblings: sk-prompt`. Drop the `deep-loop-runtime Ōåö deep-loop-workflows` edges entirely ŌĆö they become intra-skill structure. Preserve `deep-loop-runtime`'s `packet_id: \"116-deep-skill-evolution\"` lineage narratively (this packet's spec.md + the new `changelog/v2.0.0.0.md`), not structurally.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n\n### Phase 1: Setup (Stage 0 ŌĆö pre-flight, no tracked-file changes)\n- [ ] Establish recovery baseline (worktree snapshot or pre-move tag).\n- [ ] Quiesce: confirm zero in-flight `/deep:*` sessions, zero stale writer-lock files under `runtime/database/`.\n- [ ] Capture baseline: `cd deep-loop-runtime && npm test` (expect 47 files/379 tests; tolerate one known rerun-clearable flake in `loop-lock.vitest.ts`).\n- [ ] Snapshot SQLite checksums + `observability-events.jsonl` line count.\n\n### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n- [ ] **Stage 1**: `git mv deep-loop-workflows system-deep-loop`; edit identity fields (`SKILL.md`, `description.json`, `mode-registry.json`, `hub-router.json`, `graph-metadata.json` `skill_id`, README title) inside that tree only.\n- [ ] **Stage 2**: `git mv deep-loop-runtime system-deep-loop/runtime`; delete `runtime/graph-metadata.json`; demote `runtime/SKILL.md` ŌåÆ `runtime/README.md` (strip routable-skill frontmatter, keep content).\n- [ ] **Stage 3a**: apply Class A + Class B path repairs above.\n- [ ] **Stage 3b**: apply the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow repairs above.\n- [ ] **Stage 4**: fresh-author `graph-metadata.json`; bump version to `2.0.0.0` across `SKILL.md`/`description.json`/`mode-registry.json`/`hub-router.json`; write `changelog/v2.0.0.0.md`.\n\n### Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] `package_skill.py --check` on the renamed hub and all 4 mode packets.\n- [ ] `find system-deep-loop -iname graph-metadata.json | wc -l` == 1.\n- [ ] `cd system-deep-loop/runtime && npm test` green (tolerate the known flake).\n- [ ] `cd system-deep-loop/runtime && npm run typecheck` succeeds.\n- [ ] `cd system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npm run test:council` succeeds.\n- [ ] `git log --follow -- system-deep-loop/runtime/database/observability-events.jsonl` surfaces pre-move commits; SQLite checksums + jsonl line count match Stage-0 snapshot.\n- [ ] A live `/deep:research` or `/deep:review` short run confirms reverse-direction `require()`s resolve at execution time.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n\n| Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n|-----------|-------|-------|\n| Unit/integration | `runtime/`'s full vitest suite | `npm test` inside `runtime/` |\n| Cross-skill integration | `system-spec-kit`'s council test glob | `npm run test:council` in `mcp_server/` |\n| Static | Residual grep for old names inside code paths | `grep -rn \"deep-loop-workflows\\|deep-loop-runtime\" system-deep-loop --include=\"*.cjs\" --include=\"*.ts\"` |\n| Live | Real loop dispatch confirms reverse `require()`s resolve | A short `/deep:research` or `/deep:review` run |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n|------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n| 001-reference-research synthesis | Internal | Pending | This phase does not start until 001 completes |\n| Git rename-detection (`-M`/similarity) | Tooling | Confirmed reliable at both directory and single-file scope | N/A |\n\n### Downstream\nChild 003's reference-migration edits target paths that only exist once this phase lands.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n\n- **Trigger**: `runtime`'s vitest suite or `test:council` regresses beyond the known pre-existing flake; residual-grep sweep finds unresolved code-path hits; SQLite/jsonl checksums don't match post-move.\n- **Procedure**: Stages 1/3a/3b/4 (text-only edits) revert cleanly via `git revert`. Stage 2 (the physical move) rolls back via the Stage-0 recovery baseline (`git restore`/reset to the pre-move tag, or discard the worktree).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->","lineStart":60,"lineEnd":168,"totalLines":168,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/plan.md","time":{"start":1783486618859,"end":1783486618876}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08955fafb0883e03016a4dd89acedc81919277243495a7fb65"}},"id":"prt_f40161ce9001E9lpQ4C39S2NAv","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4015fc72001ZYPVcn7DwPPQdc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486618888,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_AcLtEtRwS9SQpc0sNzbA04Iu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md","offset":54,"limit":180},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n54: <!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n55: ## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n56: \n57: ### Problem Statement\n58: 948 non-noise references to `deep-loop-workflows`/`deep-loop-runtime` exist outside the two skills' own folders ŌĆö across `/deep:*` commands (434 hits, 24 files), doctor (15 hits incl. hardcoded constants), agents (36 hits across 2 real, non-symlinked trees), READMEs (root + 6 others), a plugin + 2 hooks, `system-spec-kit` (115 hits incl. a constitutional enforcement doc), and ŌĆö highest-risk ŌĆö `system-skill-advisor`'s routing corpus, which encodes the skill name as ground-truth labels in 3 fixture files plus 2 hardcoded scorer constants with no drift-guard between them.\n59: \n60: ### Purpose\n61: Migrate every reference to the new `system-deep-loop` identity while freezing the user-facing surface (command names, agent names, mode-packet folder names) stable, in a dependency-respecting stage order, with an explicit accuracy re-baseline for the advisor corpus rather than a blind find/replace.\n62: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n63: \n64: ---\n65: \n66: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n67: ## 3. SCOPE\n68: \n69: ### In Scope\n70: - Identity-only rename: skill folder name, `mode-registry.json`/`hub-router.json` `skill` fields, `description.json` name/keywords, all `graph-metadata.json` edges (6+ sibling skills), hardcoded skill-id constants in `.py`/`.ts`/`.js`/`.cjs` files.\n71: - Compiled command-contract regeneration (never hand-edited).\n72: - `.opencode/agents/**` + `.claude/agents/**` (real duplicate, both edited).\n73: - READMEs, plugin, git hooks, CI workflow.\n74: - `system-skill-advisor`'s routing corpus: field-scoped label rename + a real accuracy re-baseline, plus the divergence ledger's manual re-approve step.\n75: - The 2 \"grandfather exception\" worked-example files, updated in place with a new prefix-exception caveat (folder prefix `system-` now diverges from the frozen `/deep:*` command prefix).\n76: \n77: ### Out of Scope\n78: - Renaming `/deep:*` commands, `@agent` names, or mode-packet folder names ŌĆö frozen (see Decision below).\n79: - `.opencode/specs/**` historical mentions (3622+ confirmed) and `.worktrees/**` (17 live checkouts) ŌĆö left as non-breaking history, flagged as a coordination risk only.\n80: \n81: ### Files to Change\n82: See plan.md's Stage C-J tables for the full, dependency-ordered file list (~948 hits across ~80 distinct files/fixtures).\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n84: \n85: ---\n86: \n87: <!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n88: ## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n89: \n90: ### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)\n91: \n92: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n93: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n94: | REQ-001 | `parent-skill-check.cjs`'s own constants fixed first | `/doctor parent-skill` self-check passes before trusting any other doctor output |\n95: | REQ-002 | Compiled command contracts regenerated, never hand-edited | `compile-command-contracts.cjs` re-run; diff against committed output is byte-identical |\n96: | REQ-003 | Advisor routing corpus re-baselined, not silently degraded | `score-routing-corpus.py --min-advisor-accuracy <Stage-A baseline>` passes |\n97: | REQ-004 | Divergence ledger entries needing rename get manual re-approve | `local-native-divergence-ratchet.vitest.ts` passes with reviewed `reason` updates, not silent drift |\n98: | REQ-005 | Both `.opencode/agents/**` and `.claude/agents/**` updated | Per-file scoped grep for old names returns zero hits in both trees |\n99: \n100: ### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n101: \n102: | ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n103: |----|-------------|---------------------|\n104: | REQ-006 | Pre-commit hook + GitHub Actions workflow updated as a matched pair | Both `MIRROR_CHECKER`/`CHECKER` paths resolve identically |\n105: | REQ-007 | Grandfather-example files updated with the prefix-exception caveat, not a blind rename | `skill-parent.md` + its 2 asset YAMLs render a factually correct prefix-derivation example |\n106: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n107: \n108: ---\n109: \n110: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n111: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n112: \n113: - **SC-001**: `rg -l 'deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime'` (excluding `node_modules`, `.opencode/specs`, `.worktrees`, `dist/`) returns zero hits minus an explicit, reviewer-visible allowlist.\n114: - **SC-002**: Advisor routing accuracy on the affected slice matches or exceeds the pre-migration baseline (not just \"doesn't crash\").\n115: - **SC-003**: `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs`, doctor's skill-graph rebuild, and a full `system-skill-advisor` + `system-spec-kit` vitest run all pass.\n116: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n117: \n118: ---\n119: \n120: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n121: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n122: \n123: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n124: |------|------|--------|------------|\n125: | Risk | `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID` is hand-authored, duplicated, and unguarded in both `skill_advisor.py` and `aliases.ts` ŌĆö no drift-guard cross-checks the pair | Medium ŌĆö one could be updated and the other silently missed | Explicit manual-verify pair in Stage C; flag to extend the drift-guard as follow-up hardening |\n126: | Risk | A naive whole-file find/replace on the advisor's labeled-prompt fixtures could rewrite historical narration or (if it existed) prompt text itself | Medium | Confirmed the skill name never appears inside prompt text; scope the replace to label field-keys only (`skill_top_1`, `nativeTop`, `localTop`) |\n127: | Risk | Compiled `.contract.md` files carry a runtime-consumed content hash; a well-intentioned hand-edit desyncs it and fails silently at command-invocation time, not migration time | Medium | Never hand-edit; always regenerate via `compile-command-contracts.cjs` |\n128: | Risk | `mk-deep-loop-guard.js`'s failure mode on a missing path is unverified (loud throw vs. silent no-op) | Low-Medium | Read and confirm during Stage C, not assumed |\n129: | Risk | 17 live worktrees can reintroduce stale references on a later merge, evading a one-time residual-grep run against main | Low | Flagged for a bounded re-sweep after worktree merges; not this phase's responsibility to fix pre-emptively |\n130: | Dependency | 002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting must land first | This phase repoints TO `system-deep-loop`, which doesn't exist as a target until 002 completes | Explicitly sequenced |\n131: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: <!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n136: ## 7. OPEN QUESTIONS\n137: \n138: - Does a singleton `deep-loop` family still warrant a `family` tag in `system-skill-advisor`'s `skill-graph.json`? Left for whoever runs the advisor rebuild in this phase to decide, informed by 001's research if it addressed this.\n139: <!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n140: \n141: ---\n142: \n143: ## 8. DECISION: naming scope\n144: \n145: **Rename the skill IDENTITY (folder, routing keys, advisor constants, graph edges) everywhere. Freeze the `/deep:*` command names, `@agent` names, and mode-packet folder names exactly as they are.**\n146: \n147: Reasoning: both source SKILL.md files already narrate this exact split (`deep-loop-workflows` = \"the public, advisor-routable home\"; `deep-loop-runtime` = \"the frozen backend it consumes\"). The `/deep:*` commands and `@agent` names sit *above* both as the stable public surface and don't need to move because their two backing skills become one. The repo has an established `system-*` naming lane (`system-spec-kit`, `system-code-graph`, `system-skill-advisor`) for exactly this kind of cross-cutting infrastructure ŌĆö `system-deep-loop` continues that taxonomy cleanly. Renaming commands/agents too would be a second, unrelated, much larger migration for zero clarity gain, since the confusion being fixed is \"two skill IDs for one concept,\" not \"the command names are unclear.\"\n148: \n149: One documented consequence: the skill-folder prefix (`system-`) and command-namespace prefix (`/deep:*`) now diverge ŌĆö this is deliberate, not an oversight, and the grandfather-example files (REQ-007) get an explicit caveat noting `system-deep-loop` as the repo's one documented exception to \"folder prefix == command-namespace prefix.\"\n\n(End of file - total 149 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n948 non-noise references to `deep-loop-workflows`/`deep-loop-runtime` exist outside the two skills' own folders ŌĆö across `/deep:*` commands (434 hits, 24 files), doctor (15 hits incl. hardcoded constants), agents (36 hits across 2 real, non-symlinked trees), READMEs (root + 6 others), a plugin + 2 hooks, `system-spec-kit` (115 hits incl. a constitutional enforcement doc), and ŌĆö highest-risk ŌĆö `system-skill-advisor`'s routing corpus, which encodes the skill name as ground-truth labels in 3 fixture files plus 2 hardcoded scorer constants with no drift-guard between them.\n\n### Purpose\nMigrate every reference to the new `system-deep-loop` identity while freezing the user-facing surface (command names, agent names, mode-packet folder names) stable, in a dependency-respecting stage order, with an explicit accuracy re-baseline for the advisor corpus rather than a blind find/replace.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Identity-only rename: skill folder name, `mode-registry.json`/`hub-router.json` `skill` fields, `description.json` name/keywords, all `graph-metadata.json` edges (6+ sibling skills), hardcoded skill-id constants in `.py`/`.ts`/`.js`/`.cjs` files.\n- Compiled command-contract regeneration (never hand-edited).\n- `.opencode/agents/**` + `.claude/agents/**` (real duplicate, both edited).\n- READMEs, plugin, git hooks, CI workflow.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md","text":"<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->\n## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE\n\n### Problem Statement\n948 non-noise references to `deep-loop-workflows`/`deep-loop-runtime` exist outside the two skills' own folders ŌĆö across `/deep:*` commands (434 hits, 24 files), doctor (15 hits incl. hardcoded constants), agents (36 hits across 2 real, non-symlinked trees), READMEs (root + 6 others), a plugin + 2 hooks, `system-spec-kit` (115 hits incl. a constitutional enforcement doc), and ŌĆö highest-risk ŌĆö `system-skill-advisor`'s routing corpus, which encodes the skill name as ground-truth labels in 3 fixture files plus 2 hardcoded scorer constants with no drift-guard between them.\n\n### Purpose\nMigrate every reference to the new `system-deep-loop` identity while freezing the user-facing surface (command names, agent names, mode-packet folder names) stable, in a dependency-respecting stage order, with an explicit accuracy re-baseline for the advisor corpus rather than a blind find/replace.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Identity-only rename: skill folder name, `mode-registry.json`/`hub-router.json` `skill` fields, `description.json` name/keywords, all `graph-metadata.json` edges (6+ sibling skills), hardcoded skill-id constants in `.py`/`.ts`/`.js`/`.cjs` files.\n- Compiled command-contract regeneration (never hand-edited).\n- `.opencode/agents/**` + `.claude/agents/**` (real duplicate, both edited).\n- READMEs, plugin, git hooks, CI workflow.\n- `system-skill-advisor`'s routing corpus: field-scoped label rename + a real accuracy re-baseline, plus the divergence ledger's manual re-approve step.\n- The 2 \"grandfather exception\" worked-example files, updated in place with a new prefix-exception caveat (folder prefix `system-` now diverges from the frozen `/deep:*` command prefix).\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Renaming `/deep:*` commands, `@agent` names, or mode-packet folder names ŌĆö frozen (see Decision below).\n- `.opencode/specs/**` historical mentions (3622+ confirmed) and `.worktrees/**` (17 live checkouts) ŌĆö left as non-breaking history, flagged as a coordination risk only.\n\n### Files to Change\nSee plan.md's Stage C-J tables for the full, dependency-ordered file list (~948 hits across ~80 distinct files/fixtures).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->\n## 4. REQUIREMENTS\n\n### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-001 | `parent-skill-check.cjs`'s own constants fixed first | `/doctor parent-skill` self-check passes before trusting any other doctor output |\n| REQ-002 | Compiled command contracts regenerated, never hand-edited | `compile-command-contracts.cjs` re-run; diff against committed output is byte-identical |\n| REQ-003 | Advisor routing corpus re-baselined, not silently degraded | `score-routing-corpus.py --min-advisor-accuracy <Stage-A baseline>` passes |\n| REQ-004 | Divergence ledger entries needing rename get manual re-approve | `local-native-divergence-ratchet.vitest.ts` passes with reviewed `reason` updates, not silent drift |\n| REQ-005 | Both `.opencode/agents/**` and `.claude/agents/**` updated | Per-file scoped grep for old names returns zero hits in both trees |\n\n### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)\n\n| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |\n|----|-------------|---------------------|\n| REQ-006 | Pre-commit hook + GitHub Actions workflow updated as a matched pair | Both `MIRROR_CHECKER`/`CHECKER` paths resolve identically |\n| REQ-007 | Grandfather-example files updated with the prefix-exception caveat, not a blind rename | `skill-parent.md` + its 2 asset YAMLs render a factually correct prefix-derivation example |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: `rg -l 'deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime'` (excluding `node_modules`, `.opencode/specs`, `.worktrees`, `dist/`) returns zero hits minus an explicit, reviewer-visible allowlist.\n- **SC-002**: Advisor routing accuracy on the affected slice matches or exceeds the pre-migration baseline (not just \"doesn't crash\").\n- **SC-003**: `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs`, doctor's skill-graph rebuild, and a full `system-skill-advisor` + `system-spec-kit` vitest run all pass.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Risk | `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID` is hand-authored, duplicated, and unguarded in both `skill_advisor.py` and `aliases.ts` ŌĆö no drift-guard cross-checks the pair | Medium ŌĆö one could be updated and the other silently missed | Explicit manual-verify pair in Stage C; flag to extend the drift-guard as follow-up hardening |\n| Risk | A naive whole-file find/replace on the advisor's labeled-prompt fixtures could rewrite historical narration or (if it existed) prompt text itself | Medium | Confirmed the skill name never appears inside prompt text; scope the replace to label field-keys only (`skill_top_1`, `nativeTop`, `localTop`) |\n| Risk | Compiled `.contract.md` files carry a runtime-consumed content hash; a well-intentioned hand-edit desyncs it and fails silently at command-invocation time, not migration time | Medium | Never hand-edit; always regenerate via `compile-command-contracts.cjs` |\n| Risk | `mk-deep-loop-guard.js`'s failure mode on a missing path is unverified (loud throw vs. silent no-op) | Low-Medium | Read and confirm during Stage C, not assumed |\n| Risk | 17 live worktrees can reintroduce stale references on a later merge, evading a one-time residual-grep run against main | Low | Flagged for a bounded re-sweep after worktree merges; not this phase's responsibility to fix pre-emptively |\n| Dependency | 002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting must land first | This phase repoints TO `system-deep-loop`, which doesn't exist as a target until 002 completes | Explicitly sequenced |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:questions -->\n## 7. OPEN QUESTIONS\n\n- Does a singleton `deep-loop` family still warrant a `family` tag in `system-skill-advisor`'s `skill-graph.json`? Left for whoever runs the advisor rebuild in this phase to decide, informed by 001's research if it addressed this.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 8. DECISION: naming scope\n\n**Rename the skill IDENTITY (folder, routing keys, advisor constants, graph edges) everywhere. Freeze the `/deep:*` command names, `@agent` names, and mode-packet folder names exactly as they are.**\n\nReasoning: both source SKILL.md files already narrate this exact split (`deep-loop-workflows` = \"the public, advisor-routable home\"; `deep-loop-runtime` = \"the frozen backend it consumes\"). The `/deep:*` commands and `@agent` names sit *above* both as the stable public surface and don't need to move because their two backing skills become one. The repo has an established `system-*` naming lane (`system-spec-kit`, `system-code-graph`, `system-skill-advisor`) for exactly this kind of cross-cutting infrastructure ŌĆö `system-deep-loop` continues that taxonomy cleanly. Renaming commands/agents too would be a second, unrelated, much larger migration for zero clarity gain, since the confusion being fixed is \"two skill IDs for one concept,\" not \"the command names are unclear.\"\n\nOne documented consequence: the skill-folder prefix (`system-`) and command-namespace prefix (`/deep:*`) now diverge ŌĆö this is deliberate, not an oversight, and the grandfather-example files (REQ-007) get an explicit caveat noting `system-deep-loop` as the repo's one documented exception to \"folder prefix == command-namespace prefix.\"","lineStart":54,"lineEnd":149,"totalLines":149,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md","time":{"start":1783486618866,"end":1783486618878}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08955fafb0883e03016a4dd89acee481919f37dfaf542f8ec2"}},"id":"prt_f40161cec001Mac0DhdWjdtWOn","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4015fc72001ZYPVcn7DwPPQdc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486618888,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Q4bexiCEw7LUdcHSRJexnwk1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md","offset":60,"limit":160},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n60: ---\n61: \n62: <!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n63: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n64: \n65: ### Pattern\n66: Minimal addition at the existing retry-exhaustion decision point in `fanout-pool.cjs`, reusing `fallback-router.ts` as-is (no changes to that module).\n67: \n68: ### Registry entry\n69: \n70: ```json\n71: {\n72:   \"models\": [\n73:     { \"id\": \"glm-5.2\", \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\", \"fallback_target\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\" },\n74:     { \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\", \"fallback_target\": null }\n75:   ]\n76: }\n77: ```\n78: <!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n83: ## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n84: \n85: ### Phase 1: Setup\n86: - [ ] Operator scope decision.\n87: - [ ] Author the `ModelRegistry` entry above.\n88: \n89: ### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n90: - [ ] Add `resolveFallback()` call in `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch; on `action: 'fallback'`, re-dispatch a new lineage with `target` as its model, same label family.\n91: \n92: ### Phase 3: Verification\n93: - [ ] Forced-failure integration test: a `glm52` replica configured to fail every attempt produces a `mimo-v2.5-pro` replacement, not a 4th same-model retry.\n94: - [ ] Existing `fallback-router.vitest.ts` unaffected (module itself unchanged).\n95: <!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n100: ## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n101: \n102: | Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n103: |-----------|-------|-------|\n104: | Integration | Forced-failure fallback dispatch | New vitest case in `runtime/tests/unit/` |\n105: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: <!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n110: ## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n111: \n112: | Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n113: |------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n114: | `fallback-router.ts` | Internal | Already shipped, unchanged | N/A |\n115: <!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: <!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n120: ## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n121: \n122: - **Trigger**: The new call site introduces a regression in the existing retry path.\n123: - **Procedure**: Revert the single `fanout-pool.cjs` edit; `fallback-router.ts` and the registry file are additive and harmless to leave in place.\n124: <!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->\n\n(End of file - total 124 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Pattern\nMinimal addition at the existing retry-exhaustion decision point in `fanout-pool.cjs`, reusing `fallback-router.ts` as-is (no changes to that module).\n\n### Registry entry\n\n```json\n{\n  \"models\": [\n    { \"id\": \"glm-5.2\", \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\", \"fallback_target\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\" },\n    { \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\", \"fallback_target\": null }\n  ]\n}\n```\n<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md","text":"---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Pattern\nMinimal addition at the existing retry-exhaustion decision point in `fanout-pool.cjs`, reusing `fallback-router.ts` as-is (no changes to that module).\n\n### Registry entry\n\n```json\n{\n  \"models\": [\n    { \"id\": \"glm-5.2\", \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\", \"fallback_target\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\" },\n    { \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\", \"fallback_target\": null }\n  ]\n}\n```\n<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n\n### Phase 1: Setup\n- [ ] Operator scope decision.\n- [ ] Author the `ModelRegistry` entry above.\n\n### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n- [ ] Add `resolveFallback()` call in `fanout-pool.cjs`'s retry-exhausted branch; on `action: 'fallback'`, re-dispatch a new lineage with `target` as its model, same label family.\n\n### Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] Forced-failure integration test: a `glm52` replica configured to fail every attempt produces a `mimo-v2.5-pro` replacement, not a 4th same-model retry.\n- [ ] Existing `fallback-router.vitest.ts` unaffected (module itself unchanged).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n\n| Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n|-----------|-------|-------|\n| Integration | Forced-failure fallback dispatch | New vitest case in `runtime/tests/unit/` |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n|------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n| `fallback-router.ts` | Internal | Already shipped, unchanged | N/A |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n\n- **Trigger**: The new call site introduces a regression in the existing retry path.\n- **Procedure**: Revert the single `fanout-pool.cjs` edit; `fallback-router.ts` and the registry file are additive and harmless to leave in place.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->","lineStart":60,"lineEnd":124,"totalLines":124,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md","time":{"start":1783486618870,"end":1783486618879}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08955fafb0883e03016a4dd89acef08191b8c1ddfe46dc66cd"}},"id":"prt_f40161cf5001BfMAhf9iAF6Bc1","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4015fc72001ZYPVcn7DwPPQdc"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486618888,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_p42TwKb2EoVVeN2imc3vV23M","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md","offset":60,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: <!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n64: ## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n65: \n66: ### Pattern\n67: Grep-before/grep-after bracketing per file category, never a blind one-shot find/replace. Category-level rule for what's safe to leave: anything under `.opencode/specs/**` is historical and untouched; anything executable, structured-data, or advisor-facing must update.\n68: \n69: ### Stage sequence\n70: \n71: **Stage A ŌĆö Pre-flight baseline.** Scoped `rg` inventory (excluding `node_modules`, specs, `.worktrees`, `dist/`) as the audit anchor. Run `score-routing-corpus.py` once, pre-change, to capture current accuracy numbers.\n72: \n73: **Stage B ŌĆö Consume the physical move (from 002).** Combine move + rewrite into one atomic unit. Drop temporary compat symlinks right after the move as a safety net for the rewrite window.\n74: \n75: **Stage C ŌĆö Hardcoded code constants** (must land before D-J):\n76: 1. `skill_advisor.py`: `MODE_REGISTRY_PATH`, `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID`, the literal skill string inside `_projection_hash()` (changes the emitted hash intentionally), `ALIASES_TS_PATH`, routing-weight tables.\n77: 2. `aliases.ts`: hand-authored `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID` constant only ŌĆö do NOT touch the generated block (regenerated in Stage D).\n78: 3. `explicit.ts`: `TOKEN_BOOSTS`/`PHRASE_BOOSTS` literals.\n79: 4. `mk-deep-loop-guard.js`: `REGISTRY_RELATIVE_PATH` constant + test fixture ŌĆö first confirm its failure mode (throw vs. silent no-op) on a missing path.\n80: 5. `parent-skill-check.cjs`: `GLOBAL_MAP_OWNER`, `DEFAULT_TARGET` ŌĆö **highest priority**, gates every other skill's doctor audit, not just this one's.\n81: 6. `render-command-contract.cjs` + `compile-command-contracts.cjs`: cross-skill relative requires + the hardcoded path manifest (in-file sed safe here, no historical-narrative risk).\n82: 7. Pre-commit hook (`MIRROR_CHECKER`) + GitHub Actions workflow (`CHECKER`) ŌĆö edited as a matched pair.\n83: \n84: **Stage D ŌĆö Structured identity fields + codegen** (depends on B+C):\n85: 1. `mode-registry.json`/`hub-router.json` `skill` fields, `description.json` name/keywords, both `SKILL.md` frontmatter, moved folders' own `graph-metadata.json` self-references.\n86: 2. Run `skill_advisor.py --emit-routing-projection` ŌĆö regenerates `aliases.ts`'s generated block AND `skill_advisor.py`'s own hash block in one pass.\n87: 3. Update `routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts`'s hardcoded `registryPath` constant.\n88: \n89: **Stage E ŌĆö Compiled command-contract regeneration** (depends on C.6/D):\n90: 1. Update `skill:`/`skill_md:` frontmatter in 8 source YAML assets under `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/*.yaml`.\n91: 2. Update 3 router `.md` one-liners (`deep/review.md`, `research.md`, `ai-council.md`).\n92: 3. Run `compile-command-contracts.cjs` ŌĆö never hand-edit the compiled output (embedded content hash).\n93: 4. `.claude/commands -> .opencode/commands` is a real symlink ŌĆö edit once.\n94: \n95: **Stage F ŌĆö Prose/docs** (parallel-safe once B's paths exist): agents (`.opencode/agents/**` + `.claude/agents/**`, real non-symlinked duplicate, per-file scoped grep verification not a blanket diff), root README + 6 others, `system-spec-kit`'s constitutional doc + references, cross-skill \"related skills\" prose (`sk-design`, `cli-opencode`, `sk-code`, `sk-prompt-models`).\n96: \n97: **Stage G ŌĆö Sibling `graph-metadata.json` edges** in `system-spec-kit`, `system-skill-advisor`, `cli-opencode`, `sk-code`, `sk-prompt`. Where a graph carries two separate edges (one to each old skill), collapse to one edge, not a duplicate.\n98: \n99: **Stage H ŌĆö Grandfather-example files** (spec.md ┬¦8 Decision): `parent_skills_nested_packets.md`'s hub matrix and `skill-parent.md`'s canonical-example sentence updated to `system-deep-loop`. `skill-parent.md`'s prefix-derivation example specifically needs its OTHER half swapped (not just the name substituted) since the equivalence \"folder prefix == command-namespace prefix\" now has one documented exception ŌĆö add an explicit caveat sentence, apply the same fix to the 2 asset YAMLs.\n100: \n101: **Stage I ŌĆö Advisor routing corpus + re-baseline** (depends on C+D):\n102: - Field-scoped replace on `\"skill_top_1\"`/`\"nativeTop\"`/`\"localTop\"` values only (confirmed: skill name never appears inside prompt text).\n103: - `local-native-approved-divergences.json`: run the ratchet test post-rename, let it fail and print its mismatch diff, hand-verify each flagged mismatch is the expected rename, then update `nativeTop`/`localTop`/`reason`/`approvedAt` together per entry ŌĆö mirrors the existing 2026-06-15 re-baseline entry's own pattern.\n104: - `score-routing-corpus.py --min-advisor-accuracy <Stage-A baseline>` to prove the number held.\n105: \n106: **Stage J ŌĆö Verification/exit gate** (always last, in order): residual-grep sweep ŌåÆ `parent-skill-check.cjs` self-check ŌåÆ advisor codegen clean + drift-guard ŌåÆ contract-compile determinism ŌåÆ routing-accuracy re-baseline ŌåÆ divergence ratchet suite ŌåÆ agent-mirror sync check ŌåÆ `/doctor:update` skill-graph rebuild ŌåÆ CI parity ŌåÆ full vitest for `system-skill-advisor` + `system-spec-kit` ŌåÆ `create:skill-parent` smoke check.\n107: <!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: <!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n112: ## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n113: \n114: ### Phase 1: Setup\n115: - [ ] Stage A: capture baseline `rg` inventory + advisor accuracy numbers.\n116: \n117: ### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n118: - [ ] Stage B: consume the physical move; drop temp compat symlinks.\n119: - [ ] Stage C: hardcoded code constants (7 sub-items above).\n120: - [ ] Stage D: structured identity fields + codegen.\n121: - [ ] Stage E: compiled command-contract regeneration.\n122: - [ ] Stage F: prose/docs (agents, READMEs, system-spec-kit references).\n123: - [ ] Stage G: sibling graph-metadata.json edges.\n124: - [ ] Stage H: grandfather-example files with the prefix-exception caveat.\n125: - [ ] Stage I: advisor routing corpus field-scoped rename + divergence ledger re-approve + accuracy re-baseline.\n126: \n127: ### Phase 3: Verification\n128: - [ ] Stage J: full 11-step exit-gate sweep (see Architecture above).\n129: - [ ] Remove temporary compat symlinks once residual-grep is clean.\n130: <!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n135: ## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n136: \n137: | Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n138: |-----------|-------|-------|\n139: | Static | Residual reference sweep | `rg -l 'deep-loop-workflows\\|deep-loop-runtime'` excluding specs/worktrees/node_modules/dist |\n140: | Routing | Advisor codegen drift + accuracy | `routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts`, `score-routing-corpus.py` |\n141: | Ledger | Divergence re-approve completeness | `local-native-divergence-ratchet.vitest.ts` |\n142: | Integration | Doctor + hooks + CI parity | `/doctor parent-skill`, `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs`, pre-commit vs. GH Actions path comparison |\n143: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: <!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n148: ## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n149: \n150: | Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n151: |------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n152: | 002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting | Internal | Pending | This phase repoints TO paths that don't exist until 002 lands |\n153: \n154: ### Downstream\n155: 005-validation-and-closeout's final sweep assumes this phase's Stage J already passed.\n156: <!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n157: \n158: ---\n159: \n160: <!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n161: ## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n162: \n163: - **Trigger**: Stage J's exit gate fails on advisor accuracy regression, unresolved residual grep, or a broken doctor/hook/CI path.\n164: - **Procedure**: every stage here is a text-only edit or codegen re-run ŌĆö revert via `git revert` per stage; the temporary compat symlinks (Stage B) provide a live safety net during the rewrite window itself.\n165: <!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Pattern\nGrep-before/grep-after bracketing per file category, never a blind one-shot find/replace. Category-level rule for what's safe to leave: anything under `.opencode/specs/**` is historical and untouched; anything executable, structured-data, or advisor-facing must update.\n\n### Stage sequence\n\n**Stage A ŌĆö Pre-flight baseline.** Scoped `rg` inventory (excluding `node_modules`, specs, `.worktrees`, `dist/`) as the audit anchor. Run `score-routing-corpus.py` once, pre-change, to capture current accuracy numbers.\n\n**Stage B ŌĆö Consume the physical move (from 002).** Combine move + rewrite into one atomic unit. Drop temporary compat symlinks right after the move as a safety net for the rewrite window.\n\n**Stage C ŌĆö Hardcoded code constants** (must land before D-J):\n1. `skill_advisor.py`: `MODE_REGISTRY_PATH`, `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID`, the literal skill string inside `_projection_hash()` (changes the emitted hash intentionally), `ALIASES_TS_PATH`, routing-weight tables.\n2. `aliases.ts`: hand-authored `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID` constant only ŌĆö do NOT touch the generated block (regenerated in Stage D).\n3. `explicit.ts`: `TOKEN_BOOSTS`/`PHRASE_BOOSTS` literals.\n4. `mk-deep-loop-guard.js`: `REGISTRY_RELATIVE_PATH` constant + test fixture ŌĆö first confirm its failure mode (throw vs. silent no-op) on a missing path.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md","text":"\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:architecture -->\n## 3. ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Pattern\nGrep-before/grep-after bracketing per file category, never a blind one-shot find/replace. Category-level rule for what's safe to leave: anything under `.opencode/specs/**` is historical and untouched; anything executable, structured-data, or advisor-facing must update.\n\n### Stage sequence\n\n**Stage A ŌĆö Pre-flight baseline.** Scoped `rg` inventory (excluding `node_modules`, specs, `.worktrees`, `dist/`) as the audit anchor. Run `score-routing-corpus.py` once, pre-change, to capture current accuracy numbers.\n\n**Stage B ŌĆö Consume the physical move (from 002).** Combine move + rewrite into one atomic unit. Drop temporary compat symlinks right after the move as a safety net for the rewrite window.\n\n**Stage C ŌĆö Hardcoded code constants** (must land before D-J):\n1. `skill_advisor.py`: `MODE_REGISTRY_PATH`, `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID`, the literal skill string inside `_projection_hash()` (changes the emitted hash intentionally), `ALIASES_TS_PATH`, routing-weight tables.\n2. `aliases.ts`: hand-authored `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID` constant only ŌĆö do NOT touch the generated block (regenerated in Stage D).\n3. `explicit.ts`: `TOKEN_BOOSTS`/`PHRASE_BOOSTS` literals.\n4. `mk-deep-loop-guard.js`: `REGISTRY_RELATIVE_PATH` constant + test fixture ŌĆö first confirm its failure mode (throw vs. silent no-op) on a missing path.\n5. `parent-skill-check.cjs`: `GLOBAL_MAP_OWNER`, `DEFAULT_TARGET` ŌĆö **highest priority**, gates every other skill's doctor audit, not just this one's.\n6. `render-command-contract.cjs` + `compile-command-contracts.cjs`: cross-skill relative requires + the hardcoded path manifest (in-file sed safe here, no historical-narrative risk).\n7. Pre-commit hook (`MIRROR_CHECKER`) + GitHub Actions workflow (`CHECKER`) ŌĆö edited as a matched pair.\n\n**Stage D ŌĆö Structured identity fields + codegen** (depends on B+C):\n1. `mode-registry.json`/`hub-router.json` `skill` fields, `description.json` name/keywords, both `SKILL.md` frontmatter, moved folders' own `graph-metadata.json` self-references.\n2. Run `skill_advisor.py --emit-routing-projection` ŌĆö regenerates `aliases.ts`'s generated block AND `skill_advisor.py`'s own hash block in one pass.\n3. Update `routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts`'s hardcoded `registryPath` constant.\n\n**Stage E ŌĆö Compiled command-contract regeneration** (depends on C.6/D):\n1. Update `skill:`/`skill_md:` frontmatter in 8 source YAML assets under `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/*.yaml`.\n2. Update 3 router `.md` one-liners (`deep/review.md`, `research.md`, `ai-council.md`).\n3. Run `compile-command-contracts.cjs` ŌĆö never hand-edit the compiled output (embedded content hash).\n4. `.claude/commands -> .opencode/commands` is a real symlink ŌĆö edit once.\n\n**Stage F ŌĆö Prose/docs** (parallel-safe once B's paths exist): agents (`.opencode/agents/**` + `.claude/agents/**`, real non-symlinked duplicate, per-file scoped grep verification not a blanket diff), root README + 6 others, `system-spec-kit`'s constitutional doc + references, cross-skill \"related skills\" prose (`sk-design`, `cli-opencode`, `sk-code`, `sk-prompt-models`).\n\n**Stage G ŌĆö Sibling `graph-metadata.json` edges** in `system-spec-kit`, `system-skill-advisor`, `cli-opencode`, `sk-code`, `sk-prompt`. Where a graph carries two separate edges (one to each old skill), collapse to one edge, not a duplicate.\n\n**Stage H ŌĆö Grandfather-example files** (spec.md ┬¦8 Decision): `parent_skills_nested_packets.md`'s hub matrix and `skill-parent.md`'s canonical-example sentence updated to `system-deep-loop`. `skill-parent.md`'s prefix-derivation example specifically needs its OTHER half swapped (not just the name substituted) since the equivalence \"folder prefix == command-namespace prefix\" now has one documented exception ŌĆö add an explicit caveat sentence, apply the same fix to the 2 asset YAMLs.\n\n**Stage I ŌĆö Advisor routing corpus + re-baseline** (depends on C+D):\n- Field-scoped replace on `\"skill_top_1\"`/`\"nativeTop\"`/`\"localTop\"` values only (confirmed: skill name never appears inside prompt text).\n- `local-native-approved-divergences.json`: run the ratchet test post-rename, let it fail and print its mismatch diff, hand-verify each flagged mismatch is the expected rename, then update `nativeTop`/`localTop`/`reason`/`approvedAt` together per entry ŌĆö mirrors the existing 2026-06-15 re-baseline entry's own pattern.\n- `score-routing-corpus.py --min-advisor-accuracy <Stage-A baseline>` to prove the number held.\n\n**Stage J ŌĆö Verification/exit gate** (always last, in order): residual-grep sweep ŌåÆ `parent-skill-check.cjs` self-check ŌåÆ advisor codegen clean + drift-guard ŌåÆ contract-compile determinism ŌåÆ routing-accuracy re-baseline ŌåÆ divergence ratchet suite ŌåÆ agent-mirror sync check ŌåÆ `/doctor:update` skill-graph rebuild ŌåÆ CI parity ŌåÆ full vitest for `system-skill-advisor` + `system-spec-kit` ŌåÆ `create:skill-parent` smoke check.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:architecture -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phases -->\n## 4. IMPLEMENTATION PHASES\n\n### Phase 1: Setup\n- [ ] Stage A: capture baseline `rg` inventory + advisor accuracy numbers.\n\n### Phase 2: Core Implementation\n- [ ] Stage B: consume the physical move; drop temp compat symlinks.\n- [ ] Stage C: hardcoded code constants (7 sub-items above).\n- [ ] Stage D: structured identity fields + codegen.\n- [ ] Stage E: compiled command-contract regeneration.\n- [ ] Stage F: prose/docs (agents, READMEs, system-spec-kit references).\n- [ ] Stage G: sibling graph-metadata.json edges.\n- [ ] Stage H: grandfather-example files with the prefix-exception caveat.\n- [ ] Stage I: advisor routing corpus field-scoped rename + divergence ledger re-approve + accuracy re-baseline.\n\n### Phase 3: Verification\n- [ ] Stage J: full 11-step exit-gate sweep (see Architecture above).\n- [ ] Remove temporary compat symlinks once residual-grep is clean.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phases -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n## 5. TESTING STRATEGY\n\n| Test Type | Scope | Tools |\n|-----------|-------|-------|\n| Static | Residual reference sweep | `rg -l 'deep-loop-workflows\\|deep-loop-runtime'` excluding specs/worktrees/node_modules/dist |\n| Routing | Advisor codegen drift + accuracy | `routing-registry-drift-guard.vitest.ts`, `score-routing-corpus.py` |\n| Ledger | Divergence re-approve completeness | `local-native-divergence-ratchet.vitest.ts` |\n| Integration | Doctor + hooks + CI parity | `/doctor parent-skill`, `check-agent-mirror-sync.cjs`, pre-commit vs. GH Actions path comparison |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n## 6. DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Dependency | Type | Status | Impact if Blocked |\n|------------|------|--------|-------------------|\n| 002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting | Internal | Pending | This phase repoints TO paths that don't exist until 002 lands |\n\n### Downstream\n005-validation-and-closeout's final sweep assumes this phase's Stage J already passed.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:dependencies -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:rollback -->\n## 7. ROLLBACK PLAN\n\n- **Trigger**: Stage J's exit gate fails on advisor accuracy regression, unresolved residual grep, or a broken doctor/hook/CI path.\n- **Procedure**: every stage here is a text-only edit or codegen re-run ŌĆö revert via `git revert` per stage; the temporary compat symlinks (Stage B) provide a live safety net during the rewrite window itself.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:rollback -->","lineStart":60,"lineEnd":165,"totalLines":165,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md","time":{"start":1783486618868,"end":1783486618880}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_08955fafb0883e03016a4dd89acee88191a9145a48835afabd"}},"id":"prt_f40161cf3001Yv8UtT66lV22iv","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4015fc72001ZYPVcn7DwPPQdc"}}
