\n\n  Line 63: No consumer action required. The script-interface contract (argv shape, stdout JSON shape, exit codes) is unchanged. TS import paths into `lib/` are unchanged. The SQLite schema is unchanged at version 2. `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` glob still picks up tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/`.\n\n  Line 78: - **Structural anchor**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md` (9-section pattern)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/07--script-entry-points/convergence-script.md:\n  Line 31: The implementation is source-backed and covered by runtime-owned tests under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/`. Treat this as shipped behavior, not a roadmap claim.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/helpers/README.md:\n  Line 22: - Parent tests README: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/README.md`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.3.0.0.md:\n  Line 11: 1. The runtime SQLite directory was named `storage/` while the sibling `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` uses `database/`. The inconsistent name made the convention harder to follow and the sqlite inside was committed to git, so external repo users shipped a stale binary database instead of regenerating a fresh one on first run.\n\n  Line 64: - **Convention precedent**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/07--script-entry-points/query-script.md:\n  Line 31: The implementation is source-backed and covered by runtime-owned tests under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/`. Treat this as shipped behavior, not a roadmap claim.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:\n  Line 1: This is the first shipped release of `deep-loop-runtime`. The earlier `v0.1.0` state was a phase-001 scaffold. Version `1.0.0` marks the runtime as populated and verified: shared deep-loop libraries, coverage-graph ownership, direct script entry points, SQLite storage, and runtime tests now live together in the peer skill instead of inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`.\n\n  Line 9: Before 118, every change to the deep-review or deep-research loop infrastructure required touching files inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`. Two consumer skills (`deep-review`, `deep-research`) depended on internals of a third skill (`system-spec-kit`), and the MCP tool surface (`mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*`) added a marshalling layer between workflow YAMLs and the SQLite-backed coverage graph. The arrangement was accumulated drift from early MCP server scaffolding; no ADR justified it. Arc 118 (FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP, user-directive override of the 117 AI Council SPLIT ruling) consolidated all deep-loop runtime infrastructure into this peer skill, removed the MCP tool surface entirely, and replaced it with direct `.cjs` script invocation ŌĆö the same pattern `reduce-state.cjs` already used. Workflow YAML calls became one-step (`bash: node .../scripts/<name>.cjs`) instead of two-step (MCP-dispatch then JSON-parse).\n\n  Line 38: - **Split by responsibility** ŌĆö Runtime-focused unit, integration, and lifecycle tests moved into `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/`:\n\n  Line 43: - The `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` for cross-package test discovery, so a single `pnpm vitest run` exercises both surfaces.\n\n  Line 59: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/` | 10 shared runtime modules moved from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/`. |\n\n  Line 60: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/` | 3 coverage-graph modules moved from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/`. |\n\n  Line 64: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/{unit,integration,lifecycle,_helpers}/` | Runtime-owned Vitest coverage for libraries, scripts, and DB lifecycle. |\n\n  Line 72: Consumers should call the four `.cjs` scripts directly rather than attempting to use the deleted `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` MCP tools. The migration source was `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`; after arc 118, the runtime owner is `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`. Workflow YAMLs (`spec_kit_deep-{review,research}_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) were updated to invoke the scripts via `bash:` blocks; `/doctor` diagnostics and the `system-code-graph` playbook scenario 009 were updated correspondingly. The `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` glob was extended to discover tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/07--script-entry-points/upsert-script.md:\n  Line 31: The implementation is source-backed and covered by runtime-owned tests under `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/`. Treat this as shipped behavior, not a roadmap claim.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-pool-concurrency-cap.md:\n  Line 45: 2. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-pool.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:\n  Line 31: Two new unit test files for the previously-uncovered `coverage-graph-query` (8 tests) and `coverage-graph-signals` (9 tests). Two weak council tests deepened: multi-seat-dispatch (2 to 6 tests) and round-state-jsonl (2 to 6 tests). All 29 tests pass via the system-spec-kit vite