{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486665904,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_jckk6iXJeVc1ccMkkjdOa0uR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":230},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47: \n48: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n49: # CONTEXT LOADING\n50: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n51: context_loading:\n52:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n53:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n54:   mcp_integration:\n55:     tool: memory_context\n56:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n57:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n58:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n59:   behavior:\n60:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n61:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n62: \n63: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n64: # SKILL REFERENCE\n65: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n66: skill_reference:\n67:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n68:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n69:   references:\n70:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n71:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n72:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n73:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n74:   templates:\n75:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n76:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n77: \n78: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n79: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n80: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n81: agent_config:\n82:   agent: deep-research\n83:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n84:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n85:   model: opus\n86:   leaf_only: true\n87:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n88:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n89:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n90: \n91: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n92: # STATE FILE PATHS\n93: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n94: state_paths:\n95:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n96:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n97:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n98:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n99:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n100:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n101:   status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n102:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n103:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n104:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n105:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n106:   run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n107:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n108:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n109:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n110:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n111:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) ŌĆö complement to the\n112:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n113:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n114:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n115:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n116:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n117:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n118:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n119:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n120:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n121:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n122: \n123: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n124: # WORKFLOW\n125: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n126: workflow:\n127: \n128:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n129:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory ŌĆö use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n130:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n131:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n132:     if_present:\n133:       bind:\n134:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n135:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n136:         artifact_subfolder: null\n137:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n138:     if_absent:\n139:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n140:       outputs:\n141:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n142:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n143:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n144:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n145: \n146:   step_fanout_spawn:\n147:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n148:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n149:     instructions: |\n150:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n151:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n152:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis ŌĆö skip phase_init and\n153:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n154:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n155:     sub_steps:\n156:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n157:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n158:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n159:         command: |\n160:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n161:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n162:             --loop-type research \\\n163:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n164:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n165:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n166:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n167:         wait_for_completion: true\n168:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n169:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n170:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n171:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n172:         dispatch:\n173:           agent: deep-research\n174:           model: opus\n175:           context: |\n176:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n177:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n178:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n179:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n180:               executor: native\n181:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n182:         wait_for_completion: true\n183: \n184:   # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n185:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n186:   # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n187:   phase_init:\n188:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n189:     steps:\n190: \n191:       step_preflight_contract:\n192:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n193:         verify:\n194:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n195:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n196:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n197:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n198:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n199: \n200:       step_create_directories:\n201:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n202:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n203: \n204:       step_detect_resource_map:\n205:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n206:         inspect:\n207:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n208:         classify:\n209:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n210:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n211:         outputs:\n212:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n213:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n214: \n215:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n216:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n217:         inspect_legacy:\n218:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n220:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n221:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n222:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n223:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n224:         on_legacy_read:\n225:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n226: \n227:       step_acquire_lock:\n228:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n229:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n230:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed ŌĆö another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n\n(Showing lines 1-230 of 1740. Use offset=231 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) ŌĆö complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# WORKFLOW\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory ŌĆö use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis ŌĆö skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed ŌĆö another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":230,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486665892,"end":1783486665903}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f1f0acb70a63af7016a4dd8c9d8b481919333cef2336b6eda"}},"id":"prt_f4016d4910010Mqq8uVCvwsAyX","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4016b3bb001UsJ4dJDkSctt5v"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486665929,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sH9ZBpzLXDuIckVZZPG623c5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":230,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n230:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed ŌĆö another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n231:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory ŌĆö best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n232:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n233:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n234:         on_halt:\n235:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n236:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n237:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n238:         on_cancel:\n239:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n240:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n241:         on_workflow_exit:\n242:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n243:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent ŌĆö safe to invoke when already released\"\n244: \n245:       step_classify_session:\n246:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n247:         inspect:\n248:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n249:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n250:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n251:         classify:\n252:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n253:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n254:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n255:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n256:         outputs:\n257:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n258:         on_resume:\n259:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n260:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n261:           gate3_classification: write-path\n262:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n263:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n264:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n265:           skip_to: phase_loop\n266:         on_restart:\n267:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n268:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n269:           set:\n270:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n271:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n272:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n273:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n274:           skip_to: step_create_config\n275:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md ┬¦Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n276:         on_completed_session:\n277:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n278:           halt: true\n279:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n280:         on_invalid_state:\n281:           halt: true\n282:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n283:         on_fresh:\n284:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n285: \n286:       step_resolve_session_id:\n287:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n288:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n289:         if_present:\n290:           bind:\n291:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n292:         if_absent:\n293:           bind:\n294:             session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n295: \n296:       step_create_config:\n297:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n298:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n299:         populate:\n300:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n301:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n302:           minIterations: 3\n303:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md ┬¦\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n304:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n305:           convergenceMode: \"default\"\n306:           stuckThreshold: 3\n307:           minIdeaObservations: 2\n308:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n309:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n310:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n311:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n312:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n313:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n314:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n315:           status: \"initialized\"\n316:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n317:           lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n318:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n319:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n320:           lineage.generation: 1\n321:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n322:           nextRunAt: null\n323:           remainingDelayMs: null\n324:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n325: \n326:       step_create_state_log:\n327:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n328:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n329:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n330:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n331: \n332:       step_create_strategy:\n333:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n334:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n335:         populate:\n336:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n337:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n338:           known_context: \"None\"\n339:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n340:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n341:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n342:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n343: \n344:       step_create_registry:\n345:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n346:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n347:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n348: \n349:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n350:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n351:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n352:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n353:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n354: \n355:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n356:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n357:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n358:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n359: \n360:       step_detect_spec_present:\n361:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n362:         inspect:\n363:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n364:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n365:         classify:\n366:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n367:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n368:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n369:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n370:         outputs:\n371:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n372:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n373:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n374: \n375:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n376:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n377:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n378:         branches:\n379:           no-spec:\n380:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n381:             seed_markers:\n382:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n383:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n384:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n385:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n386:             set:\n387:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n388:               validate_spec_doc: true\n389:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n390:           spec-present:\n391:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n392:             set:\n393:               validate_spec_doc: true\n394:             idempotency_check:\n395:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n396:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n397:               if_match:\n398:                 skip_append: true\n399:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n400:               if_no_match:\n401:                 append_only:\n402:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n403:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n404:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n405:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n406:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n407:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n408:             verify_markers:\n409:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n410:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n411:             set:\n412:               validate_spec_doc: false\n413:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n414:           conflict-detected:\n415:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n416:             halt: true\n417: \n418:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n419:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n420:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n421:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n422:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n423: \n424:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n425:         action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n426:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n427:         canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n428:         command: |\n429:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n430:           import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n431: \n432:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n433:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n434: \n435:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n436:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n437:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n438:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n439:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n440:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n441:           const row = {\n442:             event: 'started',\n443:             label: 'single',\n444:             at: timestamp,\n445:             duration_ms: 0,\n446:             loop_type: 'research',\n447:             sessionId,\n448:             generation,\n449:             gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n\n(Showing lines 230-449 of 1740. Use offset=450 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed ŌĆö another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory ŌĆö best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent ŌĆö safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed ŌĆö another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory ŌĆö best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent ŌĆö safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md ┬¦Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          minIterations: 3\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md ┬¦\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          convergenceMode: \"default\"\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          minIdeaObservations: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n          nextRunAt: null\n          remainingDelayMs: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'started',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: 0,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },","lineStart":230,"lineEnd":449,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486665913,"end":1783486665927}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f1f0acb70a63af7016a4dd8c9d8c48191afa21c55ad80299b"}},"id":"prt_f4016d4a6001rTc45RJ7ylsnr8","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4016b3bb001UsJ4dJDkSctt5v"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486665929,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_TdeiQlla4HdYY8mAHaEJEmt3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1260,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1260:           - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n1261: \n1262:       step_generate_dashboard:\n1263:         action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n1264:         read:\n1265:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1266:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1267:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1268:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n1269:         output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n1270:         note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n1271: \n1272:       step_update_tracking:\n1273:         action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n1274:         set:\n1275:           current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n1276:           stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n1277:         log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n1278: \n1279:       step_loop_decision:\n1280:         action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n1281:         goto: step_read_state\n1282: \n1283:   # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n1284:   # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n1285:   # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n1286:   phase_synthesis:\n1287:     purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n1288:     steps:\n1289: \n1290:       step_fanout_merge:\n1291:         description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n1292:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n1293:         command: |\n1294:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n1295:             --loop-type research \\\n1296:             --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n1297:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n1298:         wait_for_completion: true\n1299: \n1300:       step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n1301:         action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n1302:         read:\n1303:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1304:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n1305:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n1306:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1307:         extract:\n1308:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n1309:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n1310:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n1311:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n1312:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n1313:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n1314:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n1315:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n1316:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n1317:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n1318:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n1319:           - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n1320: \n1321:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1322:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1323:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1324:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1325: \n1326:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1327:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1328:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1329:         read:\n1330:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1331:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1332:         write:\n1333:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1334:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1335: \n1336:       step_compile_research:\n1337:         action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n1338:         instructions: |\n1339:           If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n1340:             1. Read current research/research.md\n1341:             2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n1342:             3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n1343:             4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n1344:             5. Add convergence report as appendix\n1345:             6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n1346: \n1347:           If research/research.md does not exist:\n1348:             1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n1349:             2. Populate sections from iteration files\n1350:             3. Add citations from original sources\n1351:             4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n1352:             5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n1353:           Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred ŌĆö see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md ┬¦Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n1354:         output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n1355: \n1356:       step_convergence_report:\n1357:         action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n1358:         report: |\n1359:           ## Convergence Report\n1360:           - Stop reason: {reason}\n1361:           - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n1362:           - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n1363:           - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n1364:           - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n1365:           - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n1366:           - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n1367:         command: |\n1368:           node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n1369:           import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n1370: \n1371:           const paths = {\n1372:             stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n1373:             registry: String.raw`{state_paths.registry}`,\n1374:             research: String.raw`{state_paths.research_output}`,\n1375:             dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n1376:           };\n1377: \n1378:           function hasFile(filePath) {\n1379:             try {\n\n(Showing lines 1260-1379 of 1740. Use offset=1380 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"          - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"          - status_ledger_progress: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event progress\"\n\n      step_generate_dashboard:\n        action: \"Generate or refresh the human-readable dashboard\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md\n        output: \"{state_paths.dashboard}\"\n        note: \"Auto-generated from JSONL + reducer registry + strategy. Never manually edited.\"\n\n      step_update_tracking:\n        action: \"Update loop tracking variables\"\n        set:\n          current_iteration: \"{current_iteration + 1}\"\n          stuck_count: \"if status == 'thought': unchanged (skip). if status == 'insight': 0 (reset). if newInfoRatio < convergence_threshold: stuck_count + 1, else: 0\"\n        log: \"Iteration {N} complete. newInfoRatio: {newInfoRatio}. Findings: {findings_count}. Stuck count: {stuck_count}.\"\n\n      step_loop_decision:\n        action: \"Return to step_read_state for next iteration\"\n        goto: step_read_state\n\n  # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n  # PHASE 3: SYNTHESIS\n  # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n  phase_synthesis:\n    purpose: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md\n    steps:\n\n      step_fanout_merge:\n        description: \"Merge N lineage registries into one consolidated registry; skip when single-executor\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-merge.cjs \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n      step_hydrate_summary_metrics:\n        action: \"Hydrate summary metrics before synthesis\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - reason: \"Use the latest synthesis/recovery stop reason if present, else the frozen default 'converged'. (Must be a member of the STOP_REASONS enum: converged, maxIterationsReached, blockedStop, stuckRecovery, error, manualStop, userPaused.)\"\n\n      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_compile_research:\n        action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n        instructions: |\n          If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n            1. Read current research/research.md\n            2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n            3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n            4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n            5. Add convergence report as appendix\n            6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n\n          If research/research.md does not exist:\n            1. Create research/research.md following 17-section template\n            2. Populate sections from iteration files\n            3. Add citations from original sources\n            4. Note unanswered questions in Open Questions section\n            5. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n          Preserve machine-owned markers so the reducer-owned registry, dashboard, and strategy anchors can be refreshed on re-run without mutating prior synthesis. (Note: `completed-continue` lineage branch is deferred ŌĆö see `deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md ┬¦Lifecycle Branch Contract`.)\n        output: \"{state_paths.research_output}\"\n\n      step_convergence_report:\n        action: \"Generate and append convergence report\"\n        report: |\n          ## Convergence Report\n          - Stop reason: {reason}\n          - Total iterations: {iteration_count}\n          - Questions answered: {answered_count} / {total_questions}\n          - Remaining questions: {remaining_questions}\n          - Last 3 iteration summaries: {last_3_summaries}\n          - Convergence threshold: {convergence_threshold}\n          - Segment transitions, wave scores, and checkpoint metrics are experimental and omitted from the live report.\n        command: |\n          node --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { appendFileSync, existsSync, readFileSync, statSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          const paths = {\n            stateLog: String.raw`{state_paths.state_log}`,\n            registry: String.raw`{state_paths.registry}`,\n            research: String.raw`{state_paths.research_output}`,\n            dashboard: String.raw`{state_paths.dashboard}`,\n          };\n\n          function hasFile(filePath) {\n            try {","lineStart":1260,"lineEnd":1379,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486665915,"end":1783486665928}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f1f0acb70a63af7016a4dd8c9d8cc819196d765ed29628b9a"}},"id":"prt_f4016d4ba0017ZglE0Bl5EAdBV","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4016b3bb001UsJ4dJDkSctt5v"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486665932,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_potfx65rEUK1EwekwiGpds2c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","offset":110,"limit":100},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n110:   review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n111:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n112:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n113: \n114: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n115: # WORKFLOW\n116: # ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n117: workflow:\n118: \n119:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n120:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory ŌĆö use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n121:     note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n122:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n123:     if_present:\n124:       bind:\n125:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n126:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n127:         artifact_subfolder: null\n128:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n129:     if_absent:\n130:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n131:       outputs:\n132:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n133:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n134:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n135:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n136: \n137:   step_apply_lifecycle_request:\n138:     description: \"Honor explicit auto-mode restart before fan-out or normal initialization\"\n139:     skip_when: \"lineage_mode != 'restart'\"\n140:     instructions: |\n141:       This is the autonomous equivalent of the confirm-mode restart choice. Run it\n142:       immediately after artifact resolution and before fan-out so old packet files\n143:       cannot be merged with fresh lineage outputs. A restart request must never\n144:       fall back to auto-resume. In auto mode, the explicit restart flag is operator\n145:       authorization to archive the resolved review packet, so do not ask for a\n146:       second confirmation. Rollback is to move the timestamped archive back to\n147:       the packet directory.\n148:     command: \"if [ -d \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" ]; then mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}\\\" && mv \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\\\"; fi; mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\"\"\n149:     outputs:\n150:       - archived_path: \"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug} when a prior packet existed, else null\"\n151:       - lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n152:     on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL; do not continue as resume or auto.\"\n153: \n154:   step_fanout_spawn:\n155:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n156:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n157:     instructions: |\n158:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n159:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n160:       A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n161:       session with a separate lineage directory and session id; it is not the single-executor\n162:       self-invocation path. fanout-run.cjs owns the stack-only recursion guard for that\n163:       first-level detached lineage and still blocks recursive same-kind dispatch from inside it.\n164:       fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n165:       deep/review command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n166:       deep-review agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n167:       sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n168:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis ŌĆö skip phase_init and\n169:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n170:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n171:     sub_steps:\n172:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n173:         description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n174:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n175:         command: |\n176:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n177:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n178:             --loop-type review \\\n179:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n180:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n181:             --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold} \\\n182:             --stop-policy {stop_policy}\n183:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n184:         wait_for_completion: true\n185: \n186:   # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n187:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n188:   # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n189:   phase_init:\n190:     purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n191:     steps:\n192: \n193:       step_preflight_contract:\n194:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n195:         verify:\n196:           - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, lineage_mode, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, stop_policy]\n197:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n198:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n199:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n200:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n201: \n202:       step_create_directories:\n203:         action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n204:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n205: \n206:       step_detect_resource_map:\n207:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n208:         inspect:\n209:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n\n(Showing lines 110-209 of 1755. Use offset=210 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# WORKFLOW\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory ŌĆö use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","text":"  review_output: \"{artifact_dir}/review-report.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\n# WORKFLOW\n# ŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆŌöĆ\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory ŌĆö use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep review artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/review/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/review/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/review_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'review')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local review owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved review packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local review archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_apply_lifecycle_request:\n    description: \"Honor explicit auto-mode restart before fan-out or normal initialization\"\n    skip_when: \"lineage_mode != 'restart'\"\n    instructions: |\n      This is the autonomous equivalent of the confirm-mode restart choice. Run it\n      immediately after artifact resolution and before fan-out so old packet files\n      cannot be merged with fresh lineage outputs. A restart request must never\n      fall back to auto-resume. In auto mode, the explicit restart flag is operator\n      authorization to archive the resolved review packet, so do not ask for a\n      second confirmation. Rollback is to move the timestamped archive back to\n      the packet directory.\n    command: \"if [ -d \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" ]; then mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}\\\" && mv \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\" \\\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\\\"; fi; mkdir -p \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}\\\"\"\n    outputs:\n      - archived_path: \"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug} when a prior packet existed, else null\"\n      - lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n    on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL; do not continue as resume or auto.\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      A cli-opencode lineage inside this fan-out is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode\n      session with a separate lineage directory and session id; it is not the single-executor\n      self-invocation path. fanout-run.cjs owns the stack-only recursion guard for that\n      first-level detached lineage and still blocks recursive same-kind dispatch from inside it.\n      fanout-run.cjs owns native and CLI lineage execution; native is run through the\n      deep/review command surface with config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir so the LEAF\n      deep-review agent is used only for individual iterations, never as a full-loop\n      sub-agent or pasted phase-running prompt.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis ŌĆö skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all native and CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type review \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir} \\\n            --convergence-threshold {convergence_threshold} \\\n            --stop-policy {stop_policy}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉŌĢÉ\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the review session and resolve review scope\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [review_target, review_target_type, review_dimensions, spec_folder, lineage_mode, max_iterations, convergence_threshold, stop_policy]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and canonical review packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist coverage-gate state\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"","lineStart":110,"lineEnd":209,"totalLines":1755,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_review_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486665922,"end":1783486665931}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f1f0acb70a63af7016a4dd8c9d8d08191813e8dc1c5f411a6"}},"id":"prt_f4016d4bc0010rp7gAJznw8NOf","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","messageID":"msg_f4016b3bb001UsJ4dJDkSctt5v"}}
