{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486806533,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeUBiiEjockj4kt1","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_RvK0rrF8KCDQnkY7bhQNZDL1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"glm-5\\.2|mimo|MiMo|GLM|quota_pool|zai-coding-plan|xiaomi","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models","include":"*.{json,md}"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:\n  Line 3:   \"description\": \"Shared small-model profile registry for cli-opencode dispatch. Each model declares one or more executor paths with their provider + quota_pool, so the fallback engine can route across pools when one is exhausted. Active small-model rotation: DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code (Kimi For Coding plan via provider `kimi-for-coding`), MiniMax-M3 (default via the MiniMax Token Plan provider `minimax-coding-plan`; pay-per-token Direct API via provider `minimax`), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via the Xiaomi Token Plan Europe provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` or Xiaomi Direct API provider `xiaomi`), GLM-5.2 (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan via provider `zai-coding-plan`). Optional unverified separate-pool stub: Claude Haiku.\",\n\n  Line 14:           \"quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n\n  Line 19:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"deepseek-api\",\n\n  Line 65:           \"quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n\n  Line 70:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n\n  Line 79:         \"quota_pool\": \"kimi-for-coding\",\n\n  Line 89:         \"dedicated Kimi For Coding subscription pool (`kimi-for-coding`), independent of minimax / xiaomi pools\",\n\n  Line 114:           \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 6 samples/cell, throttled serial real kimi-for-coding/k2p7 dispatches. (The 4th fixture hard-roman-to-int was excluded - its run stalled under orchestration churn; the 3-fixture result is conclusive.) Unlike the saturated run 006, correctness SEPARATED here. Per-framework correctness (n=18): tidd-ec 1.0 = race 1.0 = costar 1.0 (perfect tier) > cidi 0.996 > rcaf 0.992. Trust verdict: TIE on correctness (the 3 perfect frameworks cannot be statistically separated, top-pair margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). The actionable signal: rcaf (the former convention default) is objectively the WEAKEST - it produced strict-validator code that missed adversarial cases - so it is retired/avoided for this model. Among the perfect tier, costar is primary for cross-evidence robustness (also MiMo's empirical winner, benchmark 004; favored by run 006's judge); tidd-ec is the most token-efficient (25 vs costar 70 median words) and is the fallback. This objectively refutes run 006's subjective gpt-5.5 judge, which had wrongly ranked rcaf/race highest.\",\n\n  Line 130:           \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 137:           \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-api\",\n\n  Line 142:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 151:         \"quota_pool\": \"minimax-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 153:         \"notes\": \"Plain `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` confirmed live (2026-06-02; re-verified on opencode 1.16.2 2026-06-06); there is NO `MiniMax-M3-highspeed` on 1.16.2. agent_policy omit-general: `--agent` is rejected on opencode 1.15.13. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high is the dispatch-layer default; `--variant` forwarding for this provider was historically omitted (unverified) ŌĆö confirm acceptance before relying on a non-default variant. Direct API path: provider `minimax`, quota_pool `minimax-api`.\",\n\n  Line 190:       \"id\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 197:           \"provider\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n\n  Line 198:           \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 200:           \"notes\": \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) via opencode provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams (credential 'Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe)'). Live slug xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro (confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13, 2026-06-01); verify the full live list with 'opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams'. Omit --agent (warns + falls back on 1.15.13). Manual direct-provider reroute uses xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined. Context window 1,000,000 tokens (released 2026-04-22). OpenAI-compatible endpoint https://token-plan-ams.xiaomimimo.com/v1; opencode cost shows 0/0 (Token-Plan subscription). --variant maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) in opencode settings ŌĆö always dispatch with --variant high (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13). Best prompt framework (benchmark 004, 10/10 real runs): COSTAR or RACE + lean pre-planning ŌĆö frame for format/brevity, not guardrails; TIDD-EC/dense ranked last; avoid CIDI (intermittent tool-only file-writes).\"\n\n  Line 203:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 207:         \"model_slug\": \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 212:         \"quota_pool\": \"xiaomi-token-plan\",\n\n  Line 214:         \"notes\": \"Live slug `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` confirmed responsive on opencode 1.15.13 (2026-06-01). default_variant high: `--variant` maps to MiMo reasoning effort (low/medium/high) and `--variant high` is confirmed accepted ŌĆö always dispatch with it. agent_policy omit-general: `--agent` warns and falls back on 1.15.13. format_mode json: OpenAI-compatible endpoint; dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized envelope. Manual direct-provider reroutes use `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` when configured; no automatic gateway fallback is defined.\",\n\n  Line 223:         \"Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) subscription billing via provider xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n\n  Line 224:         \"separate quota pool (xiaomi-token-plan) independent of minimax / cognition pools\",\n\n  Line 225:         \"manual direct-provider reroute available at xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro when configured\"\n\n  Line 231:         \"visual/illustration tasks: over-accents ŌĆö spreads orange/gold across most cards, weak color restraint despite clean shapes and a reserved-accent brief (informal bento bake-off, n=1 fixture, 2026-06-22; see references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md)\"\n\n  Line 247:           \"sample\": \"10/10 real MiMo-V2.5-Pro runs at --variant high\",\n\n  Line 250:         \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md\",\n\n  Line 255:       \"id\": \"glm-5.2\",\n\n  Line 262:           \"provider\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n\n  Line 263:           \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n\n  Line 265:           \"notes\": \"Z.AI GLM Coding Plan (subscription) via opencode provider `zai-coding-plan` (auth credential 'Z.AI Coding Plan'). Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2`; confirmed present via `opencode models zai-coding-plan` 2026-06-28 ŌåÆ glm-4.5-air/glm-4.7/glm-5-turbo/glm-5.1/glm-5.2/glm-5v-turbo. Flagship long-horizon coding model (supersedes the gateway-only glm-5.1 removed in cli-opencode v1.3.15.0). context_length 1,000,000 / 131,072 output per Z.AI docs ŌĆö opencode `models` did not expose limits, re-verify. Omit `--agent` at top level. GLM has native `reasoning_effort` (high/max); whether opencode `--variant` forwards to it is unverified ŌĆö smoke-test before relying on it. Thinking is on by default and the Coding Plan endpoint preserves thinking. Re-verify the live slug before automation ŌĆö Z.AI ids drift (provider also serves glm-4.7 / glm-5.1 / glm-5-turbo).\"\n\n  Line 268:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n\n  Line 272:         \"model_slug\": \"zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2\",\n\n  Line 277:         \"quota_pool\": \"zai-coding-plan\",\n\n  Line 283:         \"vision\": \"native vision-to-code; image input via the direct Z.AI Coding Plan multimodal API (base64 image_url block at https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions) ŌĆö opencode `--file` does NOT deliver images to this provider per upstream #20802; confirmed live 2026-06-28; see references/models/glm-5.2.md ┬¦7\",\n\n  Line 284:         \"notes\": \"Live slug `zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2` confirmed present 2026-06-28 (`opencode models zai-coding-plan`). agent_policy omit-general: do not pass `--agent` at the top level. format_mode json: dispatch via `opencode run --format json` for the normalized token/cost/latency envelope. default_variant high + variant_status accepted-unverified: GLM's native `reasoning_effort` has high/max, but whether opencode `--variant high/max` forwards to it is not confirmed ŌĆö smoke-test, do not depend on it. Subscription billing: confirm dispatch cost via smoke test. GLM dispatch quirks (Z.AI docs): thinking on by default + preserved thinking on the Coding Plan endpoint; function-calling `tool_choice` only `auto`; streaming tool calls need `tool_stream=true`. Re-verify slug before dispatch (Z.AI ids drift).\"\n\n  Line 287:         \"dedicated Z.AI GLM Coding Plan subscription pool (`zai-coding-plan`), independent of kimi / minimax / xiaomi pools\",\n\n  Line 288:         \"flagship long-horizon coding model (Z.AI docs: Terminal-Bench 2.1 81.0, SWE-bench Pro 62.1 ŌĆö both above GLM-5.1)\",\n\n  Line 294:         \"single executor path (no fallback if the zai-coding-plan pool is exhausted)\",\n\n  Line 296:         \"--variant Ōåö reasoning_effort mapping unverified (GLM has native high/max; opencode forwarding not confirmed)\",\n\n  Line 311:           \"benchmark\": \"008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework\",\n\n  Line 314:           \"sample\": \"5-framework bakeoff on invalid-dominant STRICT VALIDATORS (validate-ipv4 + validate-date + validate-semver), 3 samples/cell, real zai-coding-plan/glm-5.2 dispatches graded by the deterministic hidden-test oracle (grader noop, no LLM-judge bias). Run status SEPARABLE: per-framework correctness costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976 (the ONLY sub-perfect framework; also worst format adherence 0.889). Trust verdict TIE on correctness among the perfect tier (top-pair costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). costar is primary as best-of-tied: perfect correctness + tersest output (13 median words vs tidd-ec 38, cidi/race 94) + cross-model corroboration (also the empirical winner for kimi benchmark 007 and mimo benchmark 004). tidd-ec fallback (perfect, 2nd-tersest). rcaf avoided (only correctness misses + worst format). NOTE: CRAFT (the phase-1 doc-guided default) is NOT in the harness framework registry [rcaf,race,cidi,tidd-ec,costar] so it could not be benchmarked; the empirical winner among the 5 supported frameworks replaces it. 1/45 dispatches was a transient infra failure (exit -1, excluded from scoring).\",\n\n  Line 317:         \"profile_ref\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n\n  Line 330:           \"quota_pool\": \"anthropic\",\n\n  Line 335:       \"primary_quota_pool\": \"anthropic\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/SKILL.md:\n  Line 3: description: Per-model prompt-craft hub for small-model dispatch (DeepSeek-v4-pro + Kimi-k2.7-code + MiniMax-M3 + MiMo-V2.5-Pro + GLM-5.2 via cli-opencode). OWNS the per-model prompt-craft profiles in references/models/ (framework + scaffold + gotchas, mirroring model_profiles.json); executor MECHANICS (binary flags, invocation wrappers) stay in cli-opencode. Advisor co-surfaces it with that executor.\n\n  Line 8: <!-- Keywords: small-model, deepseek-v4-pro, kimi-k2.7-code, kimi-for-coding, minimax-m3, minimax-coding-plan, minimax-token-plan, minimax-api, glm-5.2, zai-coding-plan, z.ai-coding-plan, haiku, opencode-go, deepseek-api, context-budget, output-verification, model-profiles, structured-permissions, quota-fallback -->\n\n  Line 23: - MiMo-V2.5-Pro (via `cli-opencode`)\n\n  Line 24: - GLM-5.2 (via `cli-opencode`)\n\n  Line 32: - Model names: `kimi-k2.7-code`, `deepseek-v4-pro`, `minimax-m3`, `mimo-v2.5-pro`, `glm-5.2`, `haiku`\n\n  Line 33: - Provider names: `opencode-go`, `deepseek-api`, `kimi-for-coding` (Kimi For Coding plan), `minimax-coding-plan` (Token Plan) / `minimax` (Direct API), `minimax-token-plan` / `minimax-api`, `xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Xiaomi Token Plan Europe) / `xiaomi` (Xiaomi Direct API), `zai-coding-plan` (Z.AI GLM Coding Plan)\n\n  Line 69:     \"mimo\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"mimo-v2.5-pro\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\", \"mimo pro\": \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 70:     \"glm\": \"glm-5.2\", \"glm-5.2\": \"glm-5.2\", \"glm5.2\": \"glm-5.2\", \"zai\": \"glm-5.2\", \"zai-coding-plan\": \"glm-5.2\",\n\n  Line 208: | MiMo-V2.5-Pro | `cli-opencode` ŌåÆ xiaomi-token-plan-ams (xiaomi-token-plan) ┬Ę `cli-opencode` ŌåÆ xiaomi (xiaomi-direct-api) | active ŌĆö Token Plan (default) + Direct API (pay-per-token) |\n\n  Line 209: | GLM-5.2 | `cli-opencode` ŌåÆ zai-coding-plan (zai-coding-plan) | active (single path; Z.AI GLM Coding Plan) |\n\n  Line 232: 5. **Honor the in-scope model set** ŌĆö DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro, GLM-5.2 active; Haiku optional. Frontier models (Opus, Sonnet, gpt-5.5) are explicitly out of scope.\n\n  Line 266: - [`cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md`](../cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md) ŌĆö Executor prompt-pack templates (MiniMax, MiMo scaffolds in mechanics form)\n\n  Line 281:     +-- cli-opencode                ŌåÉ owns MECHANICS: DeepSeek/Kimi/MiniMax/MiMo flags + permissions\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/README.md:\n  Line 25: | **Works on** | DeepSeek-v4-pro, Kimi-k2.7-code, MiniMax-M3, MiMo-V2.5-Pro and optional Haiku |\n\n  Line 34: Small models do not all want the same prompt shape. MiMo performs best with COSTAR and a lean plan. Kimi-k2.7-code uses COSTAR with TIDD-EC fallback and explicitly avoids RCAF. MiniMax wants TIDD-EC and a dense plan. DeepSeek remains the default-unverified RCAF case. Guess wrong and the model underperforms or ignores half the instructions. Without one source of truth, each dispatch reinvents the framework choice. The fix is a single hub that records each model's framework, scaffold and known traps.\n\n  Line 52: python3 .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py \"dispatch mimo-v2.5-pro through cli-opencode\" --threshold 0.8\n\n  Line 78: - The pre-planning density: dense for MiniMax (the model needs structure up front), lean for MiMo (the model prefers a light touch), medium for the RCAF default set.\n\n  Line 93: | mimo-v2.5-pro | COSTAR (fallback RACE, avoid TIDD-EC and CIDI) | lean | Empirical (benchmark 004) |\n\n  Line 95: RCAF is the default only for DeepSeek's default-unverified profile. TIDD-EC is the MiniMax choice, backed by a benchmark run. COSTAR is the MiMo and Kimi choice; Kimi uses TIDD-EC as fallback and avoids RCAF based on benchmark 007. The profiles cite their evidence. The generic framework definitions (the closed seven-framework set: RCAF, COSTAR, RACE, CIDI, TIDD-EC, CRISPE, CRAFT) are defined once in `sk-prompt`. This hub only records the per-model choice.\n\n  Line 169: A: Yes. The default is RCAF because it works for most models without special tuning. MiniMax and MiMo have empirical evidence that other frameworks perform better. Check the profile for the model you are dispatching. If it says something other than RCAF, use that.\n\n  Line 175: The model index and registry record benchmark-backed framework assignments for MiniMax, MiMo and Kimi. DeepSeek's RCAF assignment remains default-unverified.\n\n  Line 182: | Benchmarks | Review the MiniMax benchmark 003, MiMo benchmark 004 and Kimi benchmark 007 evidence cited by `references/models/_index.md` and `assets/model_profiles.json` |\n\n  Line 196: | [`benchmarks/`](./benchmarks/) | Framework bake-off run data and synthesis for MiniMax and MiMo |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/description.json:\n  Line 3:   \"description\": \"Per-model prompt-craft hub covering DeepSeek-v4-pro + Kimi-k2.7-code + MiniMax-M3 + MiMo-V2.5-Pro via cli-opencode (DeepSeek API + opencode-go + Kimi For Coding kimi-for-coding + MiniMax Token Plan minimax-coding-plan / MiniMax Direct API minimax + Xiaomi Token Plan xiaomi-token-plan-ams / Xiaomi Direct API xiaomi mimo-v2.5-pro) dispatch paths. Gives the skill advisor one discoverable routing anchor for small-model dispatch alongside cli-opencode.\",\n\n  Line 20:     \"mimo\",\n\n  Line 21:     \"mimo-v2.5-pro\",\n\n  Line 22:     \"xiaomi\",\n\n  Line 23:     \"xiaomi-token-plan-ams\",\n\n  Line 24:     \"xiaomi token plan\",\n\n  Line 25:     \"xiaomi-api\",\n\n  Line 26:     \"xiaomi api\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/quota_fallback.md:\n  Line 26: - `primary_quota_pool`\n\n  Line 27: - `executors[].quota_pool`\n\n  Line 60: > The user's actual model rotation is small-only: DeepSeek-v4-pro (deepseek-api pool), Kimi-k2.7-code (kimi-for-coding pool), MiniMax-M3 (minimax-token-plan primary pool, minimax-api secondary executor pool), MiMo-V2.5-Pro (xiaomi-token-plan pool), with optional future Claude Haiku. There are no frontier models (Opus / Sonnet / gpt-5.5) in scope to escalate to. The original Phase D plan assumed a small-to-frontier escalation chain; that assumption is gone. Naive \"pick another model\" routing on hard-fail would just pick a same-pool sibling, accomplishing nothing while spending more quota.\n\n  Line 76: | `xiaomi-token-plan` | `mimo-v2.5-pro` | none | Xiaomi Token Plan Europe. |\n\n  Line 104: 3. Read the failed model's `primary_quota_pool`.\n\n  Line 109: 8. Compare `target.primary_quota_pool` with `failed.primary_quota_pool`.\n\n  Line 132: